2173/// If we have a conditional branch on a PHI node value that is defined in the
2174/// same block as the branch and if any PHI entries are constants, thread edges
2175/// corresponding to that entry to be branches to their ultimate destination.
2176static bool FoldCondBranchOnPHI(BranchInst *BI, const DataLayout &DL,
2177 AssumptionCache *AC) {
2178 BasicBlock *BB = BI->getParent();
2179 PHINode *PN = dyn_cast<PHINode>(BI->getCondition());
2180 // NOTE: we currently cannot transform this case if the PHI node is used
2181 // outside of the block.
2182 if (!PN || PN->getParent() != BB || !PN->hasOneUse())
2183 return false;
2184
2185 // Degenerate case of a single entry PHI.
2186 if (PN->getNumIncomingValues() == 1) {
2187 FoldSingleEntryPHINodes(PN->getParent());
2188 return true;
2189 }
2190
2191 // Now we know that this block has multiple preds and two succs.
2192 if (!BlockIsSimpleEnoughToThreadThrough(BB))
2193 return false;
2194
2195 // Can't fold blocks that contain noduplicate or convergent calls.
2196 if (any_of(*BB, [](const Instruction &I) {
2197 const CallInst *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(&I);
2198 return CI && (CI->cannotDuplicate() || CI->isConvergent());
2199 }))
2200 return false;
2201
2202 // Okay, this is a simple enough basic block. See if any phi values are
2203 // constants.
2204 for (unsigned i = 0, e = PN->getNumIncomingValues(); i != e; ++i) {
2205 ConstantInt *CB = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(PN->getIncomingValue(i));
2206 if (!CB || !CB->getType()->isIntegerTy(1))
2207 continue;
2208
2209 // Okay, we now know that all edges from PredBB should be revectored to
2210 // branch to RealDest.
2211 BasicBlock *PredBB = PN->getIncomingBlock(i);
2212 BasicBlock *RealDest = BI->getSuccessor(!CB->getZExtValue());
2213
2214 if (RealDest == BB)
2215 continue; // Skip self loops.
2216 // Skip if the predecessor's terminator is an indirect branch.
2217 if (isa<IndirectBrInst>(PredBB->getTerminator()))
2218 continue;
2219
2220 // The dest block might have PHI nodes, other predecessors and other
2221 // difficult cases. Instead of being smart about this, just insert a new
2222 // block that jumps to the destination block, effectively splitting
2223 // the edge we are about to create.
2224 BasicBlock *EdgeBB =
2225 BasicBlock::Create(BB->getContext(), RealDest->getName() + ".critedge",
2226 RealDest->getParent(), RealDest);
2227 BranchInst *CritEdgeBranch = BranchInst::Create(RealDest, EdgeBB);
2228 CritEdgeBranch->setDebugLoc(BI->getDebugLoc());
2229
2230 // Update PHI nodes.
2231 AddPredecessorToBlock(RealDest, EdgeBB, BB);
2232
2233 // BB may have instructions that are being threaded over. Clone these
2234 // instructions into EdgeBB. We know that there will be no uses of the
2235 // cloned instructions outside of EdgeBB.
2236 BasicBlock::iterator InsertPt = EdgeBB->begin();
2237 DenseMap<Value *, Value *> TranslateMap; // Track translated values.
2238 for (BasicBlock::iterator BBI = BB->begin(); &*BBI != BI; ++BBI) {
2239 if (PHINode *PN = dyn_cast<PHINode>(BBI)) {
2240 TranslateMap[PN] = PN->getIncomingValueForBlock(PredBB);
2241 continue;
2242 }
2243 // Clone the instruction.
2244 Instruction *N = BBI->clone();
2245 if (BBI->hasName())
2246 N->setName(BBI->getName() + ".c");
2247
2248 // Update operands due to translation.
2249 for (User::op_iterator i = N->op_begin(), e = N->op_end(); i != e; ++i) {
2250 DenseMap<Value *, Value *>::iterator PI = TranslateMap.find(*i);
2251 if (PI != TranslateMap.end())
2252 *i = PI->second;
2253 }
2254
2255 // Check for trivial simplification.
2256 if (Value *V = SimplifyInstruction(N, {DL, nullptr, nullptr, AC})) {
2257 if (!BBI->use_empty())
2258 TranslateMap[&*BBI] = V;
2259 if (!N->mayHaveSideEffects()) {
2260 N->deleteValue(); // Instruction folded away, don't need actual inst
2261 N = nullptr;
2262 }
2263 } else {
2264 if (!BBI->use_empty())
2265 TranslateMap[&*BBI] = N;
2266 }
2267 // Insert the new instruction into its new home.
2268 if (N)
2269 EdgeBB->getInstList().insert(InsertPt, N);
2270
2271 // Register the new instruction with the assumption cache if necessary.
2272 if (auto *II = dyn_cast_or_null<IntrinsicInst>(N))
2273 if (II->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::assume)
2274 AC->registerAssumption(II);
2275 }
2276
2277 // Loop over all of the edges from PredBB to BB, changing them to branch
2278 // to EdgeBB instead.
2279 Instruction *PredBBTI = PredBB->getTerminator();
2280 for (unsigned i = 0, e = PredBBTI->getNumSuccessors(); i != e; ++i)
2281 if (PredBBTI->getSuccessor(i) == BB) {
2282 BB->removePredecessor(PredBB);
2283 PredBBTI->setSuccessor(i, EdgeBB);
2284 }
2285
2286 // Recurse, simplifying any other constants.
2287 return FoldCondBranchOnPHI(BI, DL, AC) || true;
2288 }
2289
2290 return false;
2291}
2292
2293/// Given a BB that starts with the specified two-entry PHI node,
2294/// see if we can eliminate it.
2295static bool FoldTwoEntryPHINode(PHINode *PN, const TargetTransformInfo &TTI,
2296 const DataLayout &DL) {
2297 // Ok, this is a two entry PHI node. Check to see if this is a simple "if
2298 // statement", which has a very simple dominance structure. Basically, we
2299 // are trying to find the condition that is being branched on, which
2300 // subsequently causes this merge to happen. We really want control
2301 // dependence information for this check, but simplifycfg can't keep it up
2302 // to date, and this catches most of the cases we care about anyway.
2303 BasicBlock *BB = PN->getParent();
2304 const Function *Fn = BB->getParent();
2305 if (Fn && Fn->hasFnAttribute(Attribute::OptForFuzzing))
2306 return false;
2307
2308 BasicBlock *IfTrue, *IfFalse;
2309 Value *IfCond = GetIfCondition(BB, IfTrue, IfFalse);
2310 if (!IfCond ||
2311 // Don't bother if the branch will be constant folded trivially.
2312 isa<ConstantInt>(IfCond))
2313 return false;
2314
2315 // Okay, we found that we can merge this two-entry phi node into a select.
2316 // Doing so would require us to fold *all* two entry phi nodes in this block.
2317 // At some point this becomes non-profitable (particularly if the target
2318 // doesn't support cmov's). Only do this transformation if there are two or
2319 // fewer PHI nodes in this block.
2320 unsigned NumPhis = 0;
2321 for (BasicBlock::iterator I = BB->begin(); isa<PHINode>(I); ++NumPhis, ++I)
2322 if (NumPhis > 2)
2323 return false;
2324
2325 // Loop over the PHI's seeing if we can promote them all to select
2326 // instructions. While we are at it, keep track of the instructions
2327 // that need to be moved to the dominating block.
2328 SmallPtrSet<Instruction *, 4> AggressiveInsts;
2329 unsigned MaxCostVal0 = PHINodeFoldingThreshold,
2330 MaxCostVal1 = PHINodeFoldingThreshold;
2331 MaxCostVal0 *= TargetTransformInfo::TCC_Basic;
2332 MaxCostVal1 *= TargetTransformInfo::TCC_Basic;
2333
2334 for (BasicBlock::iterator II = BB->begin(); isa<PHINode>(II);) {
2335 PHINode *PN = cast<PHINode>(II++);
2336 if (Value *V = SimplifyInstruction(PN, {DL, PN})) {
2337 PN->replaceAllUsesWith(V);
2338 PN->eraseFromParent();
2339 continue;
2340 }
2341
2342 if (!DominatesMergePoint(PN->getIncomingValue(0), BB, AggressiveInsts,
2343 MaxCostVal0, TTI) ||
2344 !DominatesMergePoint(PN->getIncomingValue(1), BB, AggressiveInsts,
2345 MaxCostVal1, TTI))
2346 return false;
2347 }
2348
2349 // If we folded the first phi, PN dangles at this point. Refresh it. If
2350 // we ran out of PHIs then we simplified them all.
2351 PN = dyn_cast<PHINode>(BB->begin());
2352 if (!PN)
2353 return true;
2354
2355 // Don't fold i1 branches on PHIs which contain binary operators. These can
2356 // often be turned into switches and other things.
2357 if (PN->getType()->isIntegerTy(1) &&
2358 (isa<BinaryOperator>(PN->getIncomingValue(0)) ||
2359 isa<BinaryOperator>(PN->getIncomingValue(1)) ||
2360 isa<BinaryOperator>(IfCond)))
2361 return false;
2362
2363 // If all PHI nodes are promotable, check to make sure that all instructions
2364 // in the predecessor blocks can be promoted as well. If not, we won't be able
2365 // to get rid of the control flow, so it's not worth promoting to select
2366 // instructions.
2367 BasicBlock *DomBlock = nullptr;
2368 BasicBlock *IfBlock1 = PN->getIncomingBlock(0);
2369 BasicBlock *IfBlock2 = PN->getIncomingBlock(1);
2370 if (cast<BranchInst>(IfBlock1->getTerminator())->isConditional()) {
2371 IfBlock1 = nullptr;
2372 } else {
2373 DomBlock = *pred_begin(IfBlock1);
2374 for (BasicBlock::iterator I = IfBlock1->begin(); !I->isTerminator(); ++I)
2375 if (!AggressiveInsts.count(&*I) && !isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(I)) {
2376 // This is not an aggressive instruction that we can promote.
2377 // Because of this, we won't be able to get rid of the control flow, so
2378 // the xform is not worth it.
2379 return false;
2380 }
2381 }
2382
2383 if (cast<BranchInst>(IfBlock2->getTerminator())->isConditional()) {
2384 IfBlock2 = nullptr;
2385 } else {
2386 DomBlock = *pred_begin(IfBlock2);
2387 for (BasicBlock::iterator I = IfBlock2->begin(); !I->isTerminator(); ++I)
2388 if (!AggressiveInsts.count(&*I) && !isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(I)) {
2389 // This is not an aggressive instruction that we can promote.
2390 // Because of this, we won't be able to get rid of the control flow, so
2391 // the xform is not worth it.
2392 return false;
2393 }
2394 }
2395
2396 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "FOUND IF CONDITION! " << *IfCond
2397 << " T: " << IfTrue->getName()
2398 << " F: " << IfFalse->getName() << "\n");
2399
2400 // If we can still promote the PHI nodes after this gauntlet of tests,
2401 // do all of the PHI's now.
2402 Instruction *InsertPt = DomBlock->getTerminator();
2403 IRBuilder<NoFolder> Builder(InsertPt);
2404
2405 // Move all 'aggressive' instructions, which are defined in the
2406 // conditional parts of the if's up to the dominating block.
2407 if (IfBlock1)
2408 hoistAllInstructionsInto(DomBlock, InsertPt, IfBlock1);
2409 if (IfBlock2)
2410 hoistAllInstructionsInto(DomBlock, InsertPt, IfBlock2);
2411
2412 while (PHINode *PN = dyn_cast<PHINode>(BB->begin())) {
2413 // Change the PHI node into a select instruction.
2414 Value *TrueVal = PN->getIncomingValue(PN->getIncomingBlock(0) == IfFalse);
2415 Value *FalseVal = PN->getIncomingValue(PN->getIncomingBlock(0) == IfTrue);
2416
2417 Value *Sel = Builder.CreateSelect(IfCond, TrueVal, FalseVal, "", InsertPt);
2418 PN->replaceAllUsesWith(Sel);
2419 Sel->takeName(PN);
2420 PN->eraseFromParent();
2421 }
2422
2423 // At this point, IfBlock1 and IfBlock2 are both empty, so our if statement
2424 // has been flattened. Change DomBlock to jump directly to our new block to
2425 // avoid other simplifycfg's kicking in on the diamond.
2426 Instruction *OldTI = DomBlock->getTerminator();
2427 Builder.SetInsertPoint(OldTI);
2428 Builder.CreateBr(BB);
2429 OldTI->eraseFromParent();
2430 return true;
2431}
2432
2433/// If we found a conditional branch that goes to two returning blocks,
2434/// try to merge them together into one return,
2435/// introducing a select if the return values disagree.
2436static bool SimplifyCondBranchToTwoReturns(BranchInst *BI,
2437 IRBuilder<> &Builder) {
2438 assert(BI->isConditional() && "Must be a conditional branch");
2439 BasicBlock *TrueSucc = BI->getSuccessor(0);
2440 BasicBlock *FalseSucc = BI->getSuccessor(1);
2441 ReturnInst *TrueRet = cast<ReturnInst>(TrueSucc->getTerminator());
2442 ReturnInst *FalseRet = cast<ReturnInst>(FalseSucc->getTerminator());
2443
2444 // Check to ensure both blocks are empty (just a return) or optionally empty
2445 // with PHI nodes. If there are other instructions, merging would cause extra
2446 // computation on one path or the other.
2447 if (!TrueSucc->getFirstNonPHIOrDbg()->isTerminator())
2448 return false;
2449 if (!FalseSucc->getFirstNonPHIOrDbg()->isTerminator())
2450 return false;
2451
2452 Builder.SetInsertPoint(BI);
2453 // Okay, we found a branch that is going to two return nodes. If
2454 // there is no return value for this function, just change the
2455 // branch into a return.
2456 if (FalseRet->getNumOperands() == 0) {
2457 TrueSucc->removePredecessor(BI->getParent());
2458 FalseSucc->removePredecessor(BI->getParent());
2459 Builder.CreateRetVoid();
2460 EraseTerminatorAndDCECond(BI);
2461 return true;
2462 }
2463
2464 // Otherwise, figure out what the true and false return values are
2465 // so we can insert a new select instruction.
2466 Value *TrueValue = TrueRet->getReturnValue();
2467 Value *FalseValue = FalseRet->getReturnValue();
2468
2469 // Unwrap any PHI nodes in the return blocks.
2470 if (PHINode *TVPN = dyn_cast_or_null<PHINode>(TrueValue))
2471 if (TVPN->getParent() == TrueSucc)
2472 TrueValue = TVPN->getIncomingValueForBlock(BI->getParent());
2473 if (PHINode *FVPN = dyn_cast_or_null<PHINode>(FalseValue))
2474 if (FVPN->getParent() == FalseSucc)
2475 FalseValue = FVPN->getIncomingValueForBlock(BI->getParent());
2476
2477 // In order for this transformation to be safe, we must be able to
2478 // unconditionally execute both operands to the return. This is
2479 // normally the case, but we could have a potentially-trapping
2480 // constant expression that prevents this transformation from being
2481 // safe.
2482 if (ConstantExpr *TCV = dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantExpr>(TrueValue))
2483 if (TCV->canTrap())
2484 return false;
2485 if (ConstantExpr *FCV = dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantExpr>(FalseValue))
2486 if (FCV->canTrap())
2487 return false;
2488
2489 // Okay, we collected all the mapped values and checked them for sanity, and
2490 // defined to really do this transformation. First, update the CFG.
2491 TrueSucc->removePredecessor(BI->getParent());
2492 FalseSucc->removePredecessor(BI->getParent());
2493
2494 // Insert select instructions where needed.
2495 Value *BrCond = BI->getCondition();
2496 if (TrueValue) {
2497 // Insert a select if the results differ.
2498 if (TrueValue == FalseValue || isa<UndefValue>(FalseValue)) {
2499 } else if (isa<UndefValue>(TrueValue)) {
2500 TrueValue = FalseValue;
2501 } else {
2502 TrueValue =
2503 Builder.CreateSelect(BrCond, TrueValue, FalseValue, "retval", BI);
2504 }
2505 }
2506
2507 Value *RI =
2508 !TrueValue ? Builder.CreateRetVoid() : Builder.CreateRet(TrueValue);
2509
2510 (void)RI;
2511
2512 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\nCHANGING BRANCH TO TWO RETURNS INTO SELECT:"
2513 << "\n " << *BI << "NewRet = " << *RI << "TRUEBLOCK: "
2514 << *TrueSucc << "FALSEBLOCK: " << *FalseSucc);
2515
2516 EraseTerminatorAndDCECond(BI);
2517
2518 return true;
2519}
2520
2521/// Return true if the given instruction is available
2522/// in its predecessor block. If yes, the instruction will be removed.
2523static bool tryCSEWithPredecessor(Instruction *Inst, BasicBlock *PB) {
2524 if (!isa<BinaryOperator>(Inst) && !isa<CmpInst>(Inst))
2525 return false;
2526 for (Instruction &I : *PB) {
2527 Instruction *PBI = &I;
2528 // Check whether Inst and PBI generate the same value.
2529 if (Inst->isIdenticalTo(PBI)) {
2530 Inst->replaceAllUsesWith(PBI);
2531 Inst->eraseFromParent();
2532 return true;
2533 }
2534 }
2535 return false;
2536}
2537
2538/// Return true if either PBI or BI has branch weight available, and store
2539/// the weights in {Pred|Succ}{True|False}Weight. If one of PBI and BI does
2540/// not have branch weight, use 1:1 as its weight.
2541static bool extractPredSuccWeights(BranchInst *PBI, BranchInst *BI,
2542 uint64_t &PredTrueWeight,
2543 uint64_t &PredFalseWeight,
2544 uint64_t &SuccTrueWeight,
2545 uint64_t &SuccFalseWeight) {
2546 bool PredHasWeights =
2547 PBI->extractProfMetadata(PredTrueWeight, PredFalseWeight);
2548 bool SuccHasWeights =
2549 BI->extractProfMetadata(SuccTrueWeight, SuccFalseWeight);
2550 if (PredHasWeights || SuccHasWeights) {
2551 if (!PredHasWeights)
2552 PredTrueWeight = PredFalseWeight = 1;
2553 if (!SuccHasWeights)
2554 SuccTrueWeight = SuccFalseWeight = 1;
2555 return true;
2556 } else {
2557 return false;
2558 }
2559}

2561/// If this basic block is simple enough, and if a predecessor branches to us
2562/// and one of our successors, fold the block into the predecessor and use
2563/// logical operations to pick the right destination.
2564bool llvm::FoldBranchToCommonDest(BranchInst *BI, MemorySSAUpdater *MSSAU,
2565 unsigned BonusInstThreshold) {
2566 BasicBlock *BB = BI->getParent();
2567
2568 const unsigned PredCount = pred_size(BB);
2569
2570 Instruction *Cond = nullptr;
2571 if (BI->isConditional())
2572 Cond = dyn_cast<Instruction>(BI->getCondition());
2573 else {
2574 // For unconditional branch, check for a simple CFG pattern, where
2575 // BB has a single predecessor and BB's successor is also its predecessor's
2576 // successor. If such pattern exists, check for CSE between BB and its
2577 // predecessor.
2578 if (BasicBlock *PB = BB->getSinglePredecessor())
2579 if (BranchInst *PBI = dyn_cast<BranchInst>(PB->getTerminator()))
2580 if (PBI->isConditional() &&
2581 (BI->getSuccessor(0) == PBI->getSuccessor(0) ||
2582 BI->getSuccessor(0) == PBI->getSuccessor(1))) {
2583 for (auto I = BB->instructionsWithoutDebug().begin(),
2584 E = BB->instructionsWithoutDebug().end();
2585 I != E;) {
2586 Instruction *Curr = &*I++;
2587 if (isa<CmpInst>(Curr)) {
2588 Cond = Curr;
2589 break;
2590 }
2591 // Quit if we can't remove this instruction.
2592 if (!tryCSEWithPredecessor(Curr, PB))
2593 return false;
2594 }
2595 }
2596
2597 if (!Cond)
2598 return false;
2599 }
2600
2601 if (!Cond || (!isa<CmpInst>(Cond) && !isa<BinaryOperator>(Cond)) ||
2602 Cond->getParent() != BB || !Cond->hasOneUse())
2603 return false;
2604
2605 // Make sure the instruction after the condition is the cond branch.
2606 BasicBlock::iterator CondIt = ++Cond->getIterator();
2607
2608 // Ignore dbg intrinsics.
2609 while (isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(CondIt))
2610 ++CondIt;
2611
2612 if (&*CondIt != BI)
2613 return false;
2614
2615 // Only allow this transformation if computing the condition doesn't involve
2616 // too many instructions and these involved instructions can be executed
2617 // unconditionally. We denote all involved instructions except the condition
2618 // as "bonus instructions", and only allow this transformation when the
2619 // number of the bonus instructions we'll need to create when cloning into
2620 // each predecessor does not exceed a certain threshold.
2621 unsigned NumBonusInsts = 0;
2622 for (auto I = BB->begin(); Cond != &*I; ++I) {
2623 // Ignore dbg intrinsics.
2624 if (isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(I))
2625 continue;
2626 if (!I->hasOneUse() || !isSafeToSpeculativelyExecute(&*I))
2627 return false;
2628 // I has only one use and can be executed unconditionally.
2629 Instruction *User = dyn_cast<Instruction>(I->user_back());
2630 if (User == nullptr || User->getParent() != BB)
2631 return false;
2632 // I is used in the same BB. Since BI uses Cond and doesn't have more slots
2633 // to use any other instruction, User must be an instruction between next(I)
2634 // and Cond.
2635
2636 // Account for the cost of duplicating this instruction into each
2637 // predecessor.
2638 NumBonusInsts += PredCount;
2639 // Early exits once we reach the limit.
2640 if (NumBonusInsts > BonusInstThreshold)
2641 return false;
2642 }
2643
2644 // Cond is known to be a compare or binary operator. Check to make sure that
2645 // neither operand is a potentially-trapping constant expression.
2646 if (ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(Cond->getOperand(0)))
2647 if (CE->canTrap())
2648 return false;
2649 if (ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(Cond->getOperand(1)))
2650 if (CE->canTrap())
2651 return false;
2652
2653 // Finally, don't infinitely unroll conditional loops.
2654 BasicBlock *TrueDest = BI->getSuccessor(0);
2655 BasicBlock *FalseDest = (BI->isConditional()) ? BI->getSuccessor(1) : nullptr;
2656 if (TrueDest == BB || FalseDest == BB)
2657 return false;
2658
2659 for (pred_iterator PI = pred_begin(BB), E = pred_end(BB); PI != E; ++PI) {
2660 BasicBlock *PredBlock = *PI;
2661 BranchInst *PBI = dyn_cast<BranchInst>(PredBlock->getTerminator());
2662
2663 // Check that we have two conditional branches. If there is a PHI node in
2664 // the common successor, verify that the same value flows in from both
2665 // blocks.
2666 SmallVector<PHINode *, 4> PHIs;
2667 if (!PBI || PBI->isUnconditional() ||
2668 (BI->isConditional() && !SafeToMergeTerminators(BI, PBI)) ||
2669 (!BI->isConditional() &&
2670 !isProfitableToFoldUnconditional(BI, PBI, Cond, PHIs)))
2671 continue;
2672
2673 // Determine if the two branches share a common destination.
2674 Instruction::BinaryOps Opc = Instruction::BinaryOpsEnd;
2675 bool InvertPredCond = false;
2676
2677 if (BI->isConditional()) {
2678 if (PBI->getSuccessor(0) == TrueDest) {
2679 Opc = Instruction::Or;
2680 } else if (PBI->getSuccessor(1) == FalseDest) {
2681 Opc = Instruction::And;
2682 } else if (PBI->getSuccessor(0) == FalseDest) {
2683 Opc = Instruction::And;
2684 InvertPredCond = true;
2685 } else if (PBI->getSuccessor(1) == TrueDest) {
2686 Opc = Instruction::Or;
2687 InvertPredCond = true;
2688 } else {
2689 continue;
2690 }
2691 } else {
2692 if (PBI->getSuccessor(0) != TrueDest && PBI->getSuccessor(1) != TrueDest)
2693 continue;
2694 }
2695
2696 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "FOLDING BRANCH TO COMMON DEST:\n" << *PBI << *BB);
2697 IRBuilder<> Builder(PBI);
2698
2699 // If we need to invert the condition in the pred block to match, do so now.
2700 if (InvertPredCond) {
2701 Value *NewCond = PBI->getCondition();
2702
2703 if (NewCond->hasOneUse() && isa<CmpInst>(NewCond)) {
2704 CmpInst *CI = cast<CmpInst>(NewCond);
2705 CI->setPredicate(CI->getInversePredicate());
2706 } else {
2707 NewCond =
2708 Builder.CreateNot(NewCond, PBI->getCondition()->getName() + ".not");
2709 }
2710
2711 PBI->setCondition(NewCond);
2712 PBI->swapSuccessors();
2713 }
2714
2715 // If we have bonus instructions, clone them into the predecessor block.
2716 // Note that there may be multiple predecessor blocks, so we cannot move
2717 // bonus instructions to a predecessor block.
2718 ValueToValueMapTy VMap; // maps original values to cloned values
2719 // We already make sure Cond is the last instruction before BI. Therefore,
2720 // all instructions before Cond other than DbgInfoIntrinsic are bonus
2721 // instructions.
2722 for (auto BonusInst = BB->begin(); Cond != &*BonusInst; ++BonusInst) {
2723 if (isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(BonusInst))
2724 continue;
2725 Instruction *NewBonusInst = BonusInst->clone();
2726 RemapInstruction(NewBonusInst, VMap,
2727 RF_NoModuleLevelChanges | RF_IgnoreMissingLocals);
2728 VMap[&*BonusInst] = NewBonusInst;
2729
2730 // If we moved a load, we cannot any longer claim any knowledge about
2731 // its potential value. The previous information might have been valid
2732 // only given the branch precondition.
2733 // For an analogous reason, we must also drop all the metadata whose
2734 // semantics we don't understand.
2735 NewBonusInst->dropUnknownNonDebugMetadata();
2736
2737 PredBlock->getInstList().insert(PBI->getIterator(), NewBonusInst);
2738 NewBonusInst->takeName(&*BonusInst);
2739 BonusInst->setName(BonusInst->getName() + ".old");
2740 }
2741
2742 // Clone Cond into the predecessor basic block, and or/and the
2743 // two conditions together.
2744 Instruction *CondInPred = Cond->clone();
2745 RemapInstruction(CondInPred, VMap,
2746 RF_NoModuleLevelChanges | RF_IgnoreMissingLocals);
2747 PredBlock->getInstList().insert(PBI->getIterator(), CondInPred);
2748 CondInPred->takeName(Cond);
2749 Cond->setName(CondInPred->getName() + ".old");
2750
2751 if (BI->isConditional()) {
2752 Instruction *NewCond = cast<Instruction>(
2753 Builder.CreateBinOp(Opc, PBI->getCondition(), CondInPred, "or.cond"));
2754 PBI->setCondition(NewCond);
2755
2756 uint64_t PredTrueWeight, PredFalseWeight, SuccTrueWeight, SuccFalseWeight;
2757 bool HasWeights =
2758 extractPredSuccWeights(PBI, BI, PredTrueWeight, PredFalseWeight,
2759 SuccTrueWeight, SuccFalseWeight);
2760 SmallVector<uint64_t, 8> NewWeights;
2761
2762 if (PBI->getSuccessor(0) == BB) {
2763 if (HasWeights) {
2764 // PBI: br i1 %x, BB, FalseDest
2765 // BI: br i1 %y, TrueDest, FalseDest
2766 // TrueWeight is TrueWeight for PBI * TrueWeight for BI.
2767 NewWeights.push_back(PredTrueWeight * SuccTrueWeight);
2768 // FalseWeight is FalseWeight for PBI * TotalWeight for BI +
2769 // TrueWeight for PBI * FalseWeight for BI.
2770 // We assume that total weights of a BranchInst can fit into 32 bits.
2771 // Therefore, we will not have overflow using 64-bit arithmetic.
2772 NewWeights.push_back(PredFalseWeight *
2773 (SuccFalseWeight + SuccTrueWeight) +
2774 PredTrueWeight * SuccFalseWeight);
2775 }
2776 AddPredecessorToBlock(TrueDest, PredBlock, BB, MSSAU);
2777 PBI->setSuccessor(0, TrueDest);
2778 }
2779 if (PBI->getSuccessor(1) == BB) {
2780 if (HasWeights) {
2781 // PBI: br i1 %x, TrueDest, BB
2782 // BI: br i1 %y, TrueDest, FalseDest
2783 // TrueWeight is TrueWeight for PBI * TotalWeight for BI +
2784 // FalseWeight for PBI * TrueWeight for BI.
2785 NewWeights.push_back(PredTrueWeight *
2786 (SuccFalseWeight + SuccTrueWeight) +
2787 PredFalseWeight * SuccTrueWeight);
2788 // FalseWeight is FalseWeight for PBI * FalseWeight for BI.
2789 NewWeights.push_back(PredFalseWeight * SuccFalseWeight);
2790 }
2791 AddPredecessorToBlock(FalseDest, PredBlock, BB, MSSAU);
2792 PBI->setSuccessor(1, FalseDest);
2793 }
2794 if (NewWeights.size() == 2) {
2795 // Halve the weights if any of them cannot fit in an uint32_t
2796 FitWeights(NewWeights);
2797
2798 SmallVector<uint32_t, 8> MDWeights(NewWeights.begin(),
2799 NewWeights.end());
2800 setBranchWeights(PBI, MDWeights[0], MDWeights[1]);
2801 } else
2802 PBI->setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_prof, nullptr);
2803 } else {
2804 // Update PHI nodes in the common successors.
2805 for (unsigned i = 0, e = PHIs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
2806 ConstantInt *PBI_C = cast<ConstantInt>(
2807 PHIs[i]->getIncomingValueForBlock(PBI->getParent()));
2808 assert(PBI_C->getType()->isIntegerTy(1));
2809 Instruction *MergedCond = nullptr;
2810 if (PBI->getSuccessor(0) == TrueDest) {
2811 // Create (PBI_Cond and PBI_C) or (!PBI_Cond and BI_Value)
2812 // PBI_C is true: PBI_Cond or (!PBI_Cond and BI_Value)
2813 // is false: !PBI_Cond and BI_Value
2814 Instruction *NotCond = cast<Instruction>(
2815 Builder.CreateNot(PBI->getCondition(), "not.cond"));
2816 MergedCond = cast<Instruction>(
2817 Builder.CreateBinOp(Instruction::And, NotCond, CondInPred,
2818 "and.cond"));
2819 if (PBI_C->isOne())
2820 MergedCond = cast<Instruction>(Builder.CreateBinOp(
2821 Instruction::Or, PBI->getCondition(), MergedCond, "or.cond"));
2822 } else {
2823 // Create (PBI_Cond and BI_Value) or (!PBI_Cond and PBI_C)
2824 // PBI_C is true: (PBI_Cond and BI_Value) or (!PBI_Cond)
2825 // is false: PBI_Cond and BI_Value
2826 MergedCond = cast<Instruction>(Builder.CreateBinOp(
2827 Instruction::And, PBI->getCondition(), CondInPred, "and.cond"));
2828 if (PBI_C->isOne()) {
2829 Instruction *NotCond = cast<Instruction>(
2830 Builder.CreateNot(PBI->getCondition(), "not.cond"));
2831 MergedCond = cast<Instruction>(Builder.CreateBinOp(
2832 Instruction::Or, NotCond, MergedCond, "or.cond"));
2833 }
2834 }
2835 // Update PHI Node.
2836 PHIs[i]->setIncomingValue(PHIs[i]->getBasicBlockIndex(PBI->getParent()),
2837 MergedCond);
2838 }
2839
2840 // PBI is changed to branch to TrueDest below. Remove itself from
2841 // potential phis from all other successors.
2842 if (MSSAU)
2843 MSSAU->changeCondBranchToUnconditionalTo(PBI, TrueDest);
2844
2845 // Change PBI from Conditional to Unconditional.
2846 BranchInst *New_PBI = BranchInst::Create(TrueDest, PBI);
2847 EraseTerminatorAndDCECond(PBI, MSSAU);
2848 PBI = New_PBI;
2849 }
2850
2851 // If BI was a loop latch, it may have had associated loop metadata.
2852 // We need to copy it to the new latch, that is, PBI.
2853 if (MDNode *LoopMD = BI->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_loop))
2854 PBI->setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_loop, LoopMD);
2855
2856 // TODO: If BB is reachable from all paths through PredBlock, then we
2857 // could replace PBI's branch probabilities with BI's.
2858
2859 // Copy any debug value intrinsics into the end of PredBlock.
2860 for (Instruction &I : *BB)
2861 if (isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(I))
2862 I.clone()->insertBefore(PBI);
2863
2864 return true;
2865 }
2866 return false;
2867}

2869// If there is only one store in BB1 and BB2, return it, otherwise return
2870// nullptr.
2871static StoreInst *findUniqueStoreInBlocks(BasicBlock *BB1, BasicBlock *BB2) {
2872 StoreInst *S = nullptr;
2873 for (auto *BB : {BB1, BB2}) {
2874 if (!BB)
2875 continue;
2876 for (auto &I : *BB)
2877 if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(&I)) {
2878 if (S)
2879 // Multiple stores seen.
2880 return nullptr;
2881 else
2882 S = SI;
2883 }
2884 }
2885 return S;
2886}
2887
2888static Value *ensureValueAvailableInSuccessor(Value *V, BasicBlock *BB,
2889 Value *AlternativeV = nullptr) {
2890 // PHI is going to be a PHI node that allows the value V that is defined in
2891 // BB to be referenced in BB's only successor.
2892 //
2893 // If AlternativeV is nullptr, the only value we care about in PHI is V. It
2894 // doesn't matter to us what the other operand is (it'll never get used). We
2895 // could just create a new PHI with an undef incoming value, but that could
2896 // increase register pressure if EarlyCSE/InstCombine can't fold it with some
2897 // other PHI. So here we directly look for some PHI in BB's successor with V
2898 // as an incoming operand. If we find one, we use it, else we create a new
2899 // one.
2900 //
2901 // If AlternativeV is not nullptr, we care about both incoming values in PHI.
2902 // PHI must be exactly: phi <ty> [ %BB, %V ], [ %OtherBB, %AlternativeV]
2903 // where OtherBB is the single other predecessor of BB's only successor.
2904 PHINode *PHI = nullptr;
2905 BasicBlock *Succ = BB->getSingleSuccessor();
2906
2907 for (auto I = Succ->begin(); isa<PHINode>(I); ++I)
2908 if (cast<PHINode>(I)->getIncomingValueForBlock(BB) == V) {
2909 PHI = cast<PHINode>(I);
2910 if (!AlternativeV)
2911 break;
2912
2913 assert(Succ->hasNPredecessors(2));
2914 auto PredI = pred_begin(Succ);
2915 BasicBlock *OtherPredBB = *PredI == BB ? *++PredI : *PredI;
2916 if (PHI->getIncomingValueForBlock(OtherPredBB) == AlternativeV)
2917 break;
2918 PHI = nullptr;
2919 }
2920 if (PHI)
2921 return PHI;
2922
2923 // If V is not an instruction defined in BB, just return it.
2924 if (!AlternativeV &&
2925 (!isa<Instruction>(V) || cast<Instruction>(V)->getParent() != BB))
2926 return V;
2927
2928 PHI = PHINode::Create(V->getType(), 2, "simplifycfg.merge", &Succ->front());
2929 PHI->addIncoming(V, BB);
2930 for (BasicBlock *PredBB : predecessors(Succ))
2931 if (PredBB != BB)
2932 PHI->addIncoming(
2933 AlternativeV ? AlternativeV : UndefValue::get(V->getType()), PredBB);
2934 return PHI;
2935}
2936
2937static bool mergeConditionalStoreToAddress(BasicBlock *PTB, BasicBlock *PFB,
2938 BasicBlock *QTB, BasicBlock *QFB,
2939 BasicBlock *PostBB, Value *Address,
2940 bool InvertPCond, bool InvertQCond,
2941 const DataLayout &DL) {
2942 auto IsaBitcastOfPointerType = [](const Instruction &I) {
2943 return Operator::getOpcode(&I) == Instruction::BitCast &&
2944 I.getType()->isPointerTy();
2945 };
2946
2947 // If we're not in aggressive mode, we only optimize if we have some
2948 // confidence that by optimizing we'll allow P and/or Q to be if-converted.
2949 auto IsWorthwhile = [&](BasicBlock *BB) {
2950 if (!BB)
2951 return true;
2952 // Heuristic: if the block can be if-converted/phi-folded and the
2953 // instructions inside are all cheap (arithmetic/GEPs), it's worthwhile to
2954 // thread this store.
2955 unsigned N = 0;
2956 for (auto &I : BB->instructionsWithoutDebug()) {
2957 // Cheap instructions viable for folding.
2958 if (isa<BinaryOperator>(I) || isa<GetElementPtrInst>(I) ||
2959 isa<StoreInst>(I))
2960 ++N;
2961 // Free instructions.
2962 else if (I.isTerminator() || IsaBitcastOfPointerType(I))
2963 continue;
2964 else
2965 return false;
2966 }
2967 // The store we want to merge is counted in N, so add 1 to make sure
2968 // we're counting the instructions that would be left.
2969 return N <= (PHINodeFoldingThreshold + 1);
2970 };
2971
2972 if (!MergeCondStoresAggressively &&
2973 (!IsWorthwhile(PTB) || !IsWorthwhile(PFB) || !IsWorthwhile(QTB) ||
2974 !IsWorthwhile(QFB)))
2975 return false;
2976
2977 // For every pointer, there must be exactly two stores, one coming from
2978 // PTB or PFB, and the other from QTB or QFB. We don't support more than one
2979 // store (to any address) in PTB,PFB or QTB,QFB.
2980 // FIXME: We could relax this restriction with a bit more work and performance
2981 // testing.
2982 StoreInst *PStore = findUniqueStoreInBlocks(PTB, PFB);
2983 StoreInst *QStore = findUniqueStoreInBlocks(QTB, QFB);
2984 if (!PStore || !QStore)
2985 return false;
2986
2987 // Now check the stores are compatible.
2988 if (!QStore->isUnordered() || !PStore->isUnordered())
2989 return false;
2990
2991 // Check that sinking the store won't cause program behavior changes. Sinking
2992 // the store out of the Q blocks won't change any behavior as we're sinking
2993 // from a block to its unconditional successor. But we're moving a store from
2994 // the P blocks down through the middle block (QBI) and past both QFB and QTB.
2995 // So we need to check that there are no aliasing loads or stores in
2996 // QBI, QTB and QFB. We also need to check there are no conflicting memory
2997 // operations between PStore and the end of its parent block.
2998 //
2999 // The ideal way to do this is to query AliasAnalysis, but we don't
3000 // preserve AA currently so that is dangerous. Be super safe and just
3001 // check there are no other memory operations at all.
3002 for (auto &I : *QFB->getSinglePredecessor())
3003 if (I.mayReadOrWriteMemory())
3004 return false;
3005 for (auto &I : *QFB)
3006 if (&I != QStore && I.mayReadOrWriteMemory())
3007 return false;
3008 if (QTB)
3009 for (auto &I : *QTB)
3010 if (&I != QStore && I.mayReadOrWriteMemory())
3011 return false;
3012 for (auto I = BasicBlock::iterator(PStore), E = PStore->getParent()->end();
3013 I != E; ++I)
3014 if (&*I != PStore && I->mayReadOrWriteMemory())
3015 return false;
3016
3017 // If PostBB has more than two predecessors, we need to split it so we can
3018 // sink the store.
3019 if (std::next(pred_begin(PostBB), 2) != pred_end(PostBB)) {
3020 // We know that QFB's only successor is PostBB. And QFB has a single
3021 // predecessor. If QTB exists, then its only successor is also PostBB.
3022 // If QTB does not exist, then QFB's only predecessor has a conditional
3023 // branch to QFB and PostBB.
3024 BasicBlock *TruePred = QTB ? QTB : QFB->getSinglePredecessor();
3025 BasicBlock *NewBB = SplitBlockPredecessors(PostBB, { QFB, TruePred},
3026 "condstore.split");
3027 if (!NewBB)
3028 return false;
3029 PostBB = NewBB;
3030 }
3031
3032 // OK, we're going to sink the stores to PostBB. The store has to be
3033 // conditional though, so first create the predicate.
3034 Value *PCond = cast<BranchInst>(PFB->getSinglePredecessor()->getTerminator())
3035 ->getCondition();
3036 Value *QCond = cast<BranchInst>(QFB->getSinglePredecessor()->getTerminator())
3037 ->getCondition();
3038
3039 Value *PPHI = ensureValueAvailableInSuccessor(PStore->getValueOperand(),
3040 PStore->getParent());
3041 Value *QPHI = ensureValueAvailableInSuccessor(QStore->getValueOperand(),
3042 QStore->getParent(), PPHI);
3043
3044 IRBuilder<> QB(&*PostBB->getFirstInsertionPt());
3045
3046 Value *PPred = PStore->getParent() == PTB ? PCond : QB.CreateNot(PCond);
3047 Value *QPred = QStore->getParent() == QTB ? QCond : QB.CreateNot(QCond);
3048
3049 if (InvertPCond)
3050 PPred = QB.CreateNot(PPred);
3051 if (InvertQCond)
3052 QPred = QB.CreateNot(QPred);
3053 Value *CombinedPred = QB.CreateOr(PPred, QPred);
3054
3055 auto *T =
3056 SplitBlockAndInsertIfThen(CombinedPred, &*QB.GetInsertPoint(), false);
3057 QB.SetInsertPoint(T);
3058 StoreInst *SI = cast<StoreInst>(QB.CreateStore(QPHI, Address));
3059 AAMDNodes AAMD;
3060 PStore->getAAMetadata(AAMD, /*Merge=*/false);
3061 PStore->getAAMetadata(AAMD, /*Merge=*/true);
3062 SI->setAAMetadata(AAMD);
3063 unsigned PAlignment = PStore->getAlignment();
3064 unsigned QAlignment = QStore->getAlignment();
3065 unsigned TypeAlignment =
3066 DL.getABITypeAlignment(SI->getValueOperand()->getType());
3067 unsigned MinAlignment;
3068 unsigned MaxAlignment;
3069 std::tie(MinAlignment, MaxAlignment) = std::minmax(PAlignment, QAlignment);
3070 // Choose the minimum alignment. If we could prove both stores execute, we
3071 // could use biggest one. In this case, though, we only know that one of the
3072 // stores executes. And we don't know it's safe to take the alignment from a
3073 // store that doesn't execute.
3074 if (MinAlignment != 0) {
3075 // Choose the minimum of all non-zero alignments.
3076 SI->setAlignment(MinAlignment);
3077 } else if (MaxAlignment != 0) {
3078 // Choose the minimal alignment between the non-zero alignment and the ABI
3079 // default alignment for the type of the stored value.
3080 SI->setAlignment(std::min(MaxAlignment, TypeAlignment));
3081 } else {
3082 // If both alignments are zero, use ABI default alignment for the type of
3083 // the stored value.
3084 SI->setAlignment(TypeAlignment);
3085 }
3086
3087 QStore->eraseFromParent();
3088 PStore->eraseFromParent();
3089
3090 return true;
3091}
3092
3093static bool mergeConditionalStores(BranchInst *PBI, BranchInst *QBI,
3094 const DataLayout &DL) {
3095 // The intention here is to find diamonds or triangles (see below) where each
3096 // conditional block contains a store to the same address. Both of these
3097 // stores are conditional, so they can't be unconditionally sunk. But it may
3098 // be profitable to speculatively sink the stores into one merged store at the
3099 // end, and predicate the merged store on the union of the two conditions of
3100 // PBI and QBI.
3101 //
3102 // This can reduce the number of stores executed if both of the conditions are
3103 // true, and can allow the blocks to become small enough to be if-converted.
3104 // This optimization will also chain, so that ladders of test-and-set
3105 // sequences can be if-converted away.
3106 //
3107 // We only deal with simple diamonds or triangles:
3108 //
3109 // PBI or PBI or a combination of the two
3110 // / \ | \
3111 // PTB PFB | PFB
3112 // \ / | /
3113 // QBI QBI
3114 // / \ | \
3115 // QTB QFB | QFB
3116 // \ / | /
3117 // PostBB PostBB
3118 //
3119 // We model triangles as a type of diamond with a nullptr "true" block.
3120 // Triangles are canonicalized so that the fallthrough edge is represented by
3121 // a true condition, as in the diagram above.
3122 BasicBlock *PTB = PBI->getSuccessor(0);
3123 BasicBlock *PFB = PBI->getSuccessor(1);
3124 BasicBlock *QTB = QBI->getSuccessor(0);
3125 BasicBlock *QFB = QBI->getSuccessor(1);
3126 BasicBlock *PostBB = QFB->getSingleSuccessor();
3127
3128 // Make sure we have a good guess for PostBB. If QTB's only successor is
3129 // QFB, then QFB is a better PostBB.
3130 if (QTB->getSingleSuccessor() == QFB)
3131 PostBB = QFB;
3132
3133 // If we couldn't find a good PostBB, stop.
3134 if (!PostBB)
3135 return false;
3136
3137 bool InvertPCond = false, InvertQCond = false;
3138 // Canonicalize fallthroughs to the true branches.
3139 if (PFB == QBI->getParent()) {
3140 std::swap(PFB, PTB);
3141 InvertPCond = true;
3142 }
3143 if (QFB == PostBB) {
3144 std::swap(QFB, QTB);
3145 InvertQCond = true;
3146 }
3147
3148 // From this point on we can assume PTB or QTB may be fallthroughs but PFB
3149 // and QFB may not. Model fallthroughs as a nullptr block.
3150 if (PTB == QBI->getParent())
3151 PTB = nullptr;
3152 if (QTB == PostBB)
3153 QTB = nullptr;
3154
3155 // Legality bailouts. We must have at least the non-fallthrough blocks and
3156 // the post-dominating block, and the non-fallthroughs must only have one
3157 // predecessor.
3158 auto HasOnePredAndOneSucc = [](BasicBlock *BB, BasicBlock *P, BasicBlock *S) {
3159 return BB->getSinglePredecessor() == P && BB->getSingleSuccessor() == S;
3160 };
3161 if (!HasOnePredAndOneSucc(PFB, PBI->getParent(), QBI->getParent()) ||
3162 !HasOnePredAndOneSucc(QFB, QBI->getParent(), PostBB))
3163 return false;
3164 if ((PTB && !HasOnePredAndOneSucc(PTB, PBI->getParent(), QBI->getParent())) ||
3165 (QTB && !HasOnePredAndOneSucc(QTB, QBI->getParent(), PostBB)))
3166 return false;
3167 if (!QBI->getParent()->hasNUses(2))
3168 return false;
3169
3170 // OK, this is a sequence of two diamonds or triangles.
3171 // Check if there are stores in PTB or PFB that are repeated in QTB or QFB.
3172 SmallPtrSet<Value *, 4> PStoreAddresses, QStoreAddresses;
3173 for (auto *BB : {PTB, PFB}) {
3174 if (!BB)
3175 continue;
3176 for (auto &I : *BB)
3177 if (StoreInst *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(&I))
3178 PStoreAddresses.insert(SI->getPointerOperand());
3179 }
3180 for (auto *BB : {QTB, QFB}) {
3181 if (!BB)
3182 continue;
3183 for (auto &I : *BB)
3184 if (StoreInst *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(&I))
3185 QStoreAddresses.insert(SI->getPointerOperand());
3186 }
3187
3188 set_intersect(PStoreAddresses, QStoreAddresses);
3189 // set_intersect mutates PStoreAddresses in place. Rename it here to make it
3190 // clear what it contains.
3191 auto &CommonAddresses = PStoreAddresses;
3192
3193 bool Changed = false;
3194 for (auto *Address : CommonAddresses)
3195 Changed |= mergeConditionalStoreToAddress(
3196 PTB, PFB, QTB, QFB, PostBB, Address, InvertPCond, InvertQCond, DL);
3197 return Changed;
3198}
3199
3200/// If we have a conditional branch as a predecessor of another block,
3201/// this function tries to simplify it. We know
3202/// that PBI and BI are both conditional branches, and BI is in one of the
3203/// successor blocks of PBI - PBI branches to BI.
3204static bool SimplifyCondBranchToCondBranch(BranchInst *PBI, BranchInst *BI,
3205 const DataLayout &DL) {
3206 assert(PBI->isConditional() && BI->isConditional());
3207 BasicBlock *BB = BI->getParent();
3208
3209 // If this block ends with a branch instruction, and if there is a
3210 // predecessor that ends on a branch of the same condition, make
3211 // this conditional branch redundant.
3212 if (PBI->getCondition() == BI->getCondition() &&
3213 PBI->getSuccessor(0) != PBI->getSuccessor(1)) {
3214 // Okay, the outcome of this conditional branch is statically
3215 // knowable. If this block had a single pred, handle specially.
3216 if (BB->getSinglePredecessor()) {
3217 // Turn this into a branch on constant.
3218 bool CondIsTrue = PBI->getSuccessor(0) == BB;
3219 BI->setCondition(
3220 ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt1Ty(BB->getContext()), CondIsTrue));
3221 return true; // Nuke the branch on constant.
3222 }
3223
3224 // Otherwise, if there are multiple predecessors, insert a PHI that merges
3225 // in the constant and simplify the block result. Subsequent passes of
3226 // simplifycfg will thread the block.
3227 if (BlockIsSimpleEnoughToThreadThrough(BB)) {
3228 pred_iterator PB = pred_begin(BB), PE = pred_end(BB);
3229 PHINode *NewPN = PHINode::Create(
3230 Type::getInt1Ty(BB->getContext()), std::distance(PB, PE),
3231 BI->getCondition()->getName() + ".pr", &BB->front());
3232 // Okay, we're going to insert the PHI node. Since PBI is not the only
3233 // predecessor, compute the PHI'd conditional value for all of the preds.
3234 // Any predecessor where the condition is not computable we keep symbolic.
3235 for (pred_iterator PI = PB; PI != PE; ++PI) {
3236 BasicBlock *P = *PI;
3237 if ((PBI = dyn_cast<BranchInst>(P->getTerminator())) && PBI != BI &&
3238 PBI->isConditional() && PBI->getCondition() == BI->getCondition() &&
3239 PBI->getSuccessor(0) != PBI->getSuccessor(1)) {
3240 bool CondIsTrue = PBI->getSuccessor(0) == BB;
3241 NewPN->addIncoming(
3242 ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt1Ty(BB->getContext()), CondIsTrue),
3243 P);
3244 } else {
3245 NewPN->addIncoming(BI->getCondition(), P);
3246 }
3247 }
3248
3249 BI->setCondition(NewPN);
3250 return true;
3251 }
3252 }
3253
3254 if (auto *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(BI->getCondition()))
3255 if (CE->canTrap())
3256 return false;
3257
3258 // If both branches are conditional and both contain stores to the same
3259 // address, remove the stores from the conditionals and create a conditional
3260 // merged store at the end.
3261 if (MergeCondStores && mergeConditionalStores(PBI, BI, DL))
3262 return true;
3263
3264 // If this is a conditional branch in an empty block, and if any
3265 // predecessors are a conditional branch to one of our destinations,
3266 // fold the conditions into logical ops and one cond br.
3267
3268 // Ignore dbg intrinsics.
3269 if (&*BB->instructionsWithoutDebug().begin() != BI)
3270 return false;
3271
3272 int PBIOp, BIOp;
3273 if (PBI->getSuccessor(0) == BI->getSuccessor(0)) {
3274 PBIOp = 0;
3275 BIOp = 0;
3276 } else if (PBI->getSuccessor(0) == BI->getSuccessor(1)) {
3277 PBIOp = 0;
3278 BIOp = 1;
3279 } else if (PBI->getSuccessor(1) == BI->getSuccessor(0)) {
3280 PBIOp = 1;
3281 BIOp = 0;
3282 } else if (PBI->getSuccessor(1) == BI->getSuccessor(1)) {
3283 PBIOp = 1;
3284 BIOp = 1;
3285 } else {
3286 return false;
3287 }
3288
3289 // Check to make sure that the other destination of this branch
3290 // isn't BB itself. If so, this is an infinite loop that will
3291 // keep getting unwound.
3292 if (PBI->getSuccessor(PBIOp) == BB)
3293 return false;
3294
3295 // Do not perform this transformation if it would require
3296 // insertion of a large number of select instructions. For targets
3297 // without predication/cmovs, this is a big pessimization.
3298
3299 // Also do not perform this transformation if any phi node in the common
3300 // destination block can trap when reached by BB or PBB (PR17073). In that
3301 // case, it would be unsafe to hoist the operation into a select instruction.
3302
3303 BasicBlock *CommonDest = PBI->getSuccessor(PBIOp);
3304 unsigned NumPhis = 0;
3305 for (BasicBlock::iterator II = CommonDest->begin(); isa<PHINode>(II);
3306 ++II, ++NumPhis) {
3307 if (NumPhis > 2) // Disable this xform.
3308 return false;
3309
3310 PHINode *PN = cast<PHINode>(II);
3311 Value *BIV = PN->getIncomingValueForBlock(BB);
3312 if (ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(BIV))
3313 if (CE->canTrap())
3314 return false;
3315
3316 unsigned PBBIdx = PN->getBasicBlockIndex(PBI->getParent());
3317 Value *PBIV = PN->getIncomingValue(PBBIdx);
3318 if (ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(PBIV))
3319 if (CE->canTrap())
3320 return false;
3321 }
3322
3323 // Finally, if everything is ok, fold the branches to logical ops.
3324 BasicBlock *OtherDest = BI->getSuccessor(BIOp ^ 1);
3325
3326 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "FOLDING BRs:" << *PBI->getParent()
3327 << "AND: " << *BI->getParent());
3328
3329 // If OtherDest *is* BB, then BB is a basic block with a single conditional
3330 // branch in it, where one edge (OtherDest) goes back to itself but the other
3331 // exits. We don't *know* that the program avoids the infinite loop
3332 // (even though that seems likely). If we do this xform naively, we'll end up
3333 // recursively unpeeling the loop. Since we know that (after the xform is
3334 // done) that the block *is* infinite if reached, we just make it an obviously
3335 // infinite loop with no cond branch.
3336 if (OtherDest == BB) {
3337 // Insert it at the end of the function, because it's either code,
3338 // or it won't matter if it's hot. :)
3339 BasicBlock *InfLoopBlock =
3340 BasicBlock::Create(BB->getContext(), "infloop", BB->getParent());
3341 BranchInst::Create(InfLoopBlock, InfLoopBlock);
3342 OtherDest = InfLoopBlock;
3343 }
3344
3345 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << *PBI->getParent()->getParent());
3346
3347 // BI may have other predecessors. Because of this, we leave
3348 // it alone, but modify PBI.
3349
3350 // Make sure we get to CommonDest on True&True directions.
3351 Value *PBICond = PBI->getCondition();
3352 IRBuilder<NoFolder> Builder(PBI);
3353 if (PBIOp)
3354 PBICond = Builder.CreateNot(PBICond, PBICond->getName() + ".not");
3355
3356 Value *BICond = BI->getCondition();
3357 if (BIOp)
3358 BICond = Builder.CreateNot(BICond, BICond->getName() + ".not");
3359
3360 // Merge the conditions.
3361 Value *Cond = Builder.CreateOr(PBICond, BICond, "brmerge");
3362
3363 // Modify PBI to branch on the new condition to the new dests.
3364 PBI->setCondition(Cond);
3365 PBI->setSuccessor(0, CommonDest);
3366 PBI->setSuccessor(1, OtherDest);
3367
3368 // Update branch weight for PBI.
3369 uint64_t PredTrueWeight, PredFalseWeight, SuccTrueWeight, SuccFalseWeight;
3370 uint64_t PredCommon, PredOther, SuccCommon, SuccOther;
3371 bool HasWeights =
3372 extractPredSuccWeights(PBI, BI, PredTrueWeight, PredFalseWeight,
3373 SuccTrueWeight, SuccFalseWeight);
3374 if (HasWeights) {
3375 PredCommon = PBIOp ? PredFalseWeight : PredTrueWeight;
3376 PredOther = PBIOp ? PredTrueWeight : PredFalseWeight;
3377 SuccCommon = BIOp ? SuccFalseWeight : SuccTrueWeight;
3378 SuccOther = BIOp ? SuccTrueWeight : SuccFalseWeight;
3379 // The weight to CommonDest should be PredCommon * SuccTotal +
3380 // PredOther * SuccCommon.
3381 // The weight to OtherDest should be PredOther * SuccOther.
3382 uint64_t NewWeights[2] = {PredCommon * (SuccCommon + SuccOther) +
3383 PredOther * SuccCommon,
3384 PredOther * SuccOther};
3385 // Halve the weights if any of them cannot fit in an uint32_t
3386 FitWeights(NewWeights);
3387
3388 setBranchWeights(PBI, NewWeights[0], NewWeights[1]);
3389 }
3390
3391 // OtherDest may have phi nodes. If so, add an entry from PBI's
3392 // block that are identical to the entries for BI's block.
3393 AddPredecessorToBlock(OtherDest, PBI->getParent(), BB);
3394
3395 // We know that the CommonDest already had an edge from PBI to
3396 // it. If it has PHIs though, the PHIs may have different
3397 // entries for BB and PBI's BB. If so, insert a select to make
3398 // them agree.
3399 for (PHINode &PN : CommonDest->phis()) {
3400 Value *BIV = PN.getIncomingValueForBlock(BB);
3401 unsigned PBBIdx = PN.getBasicBlockIndex(PBI->getParent());
3402 Value *PBIV = PN.getIncomingValue(PBBIdx);
3403 if (BIV != PBIV) {
3404 // Insert a select in PBI to pick the right value.
3405 SelectInst *NV = cast<SelectInst>(
3406 Builder.CreateSelect(PBICond, PBIV, BIV, PBIV->getName() + ".mux"));
3407 PN.setIncomingValue(PBBIdx, NV);
3408 // Although the select has the same condition as PBI, the original branch
3409 // weights for PBI do not apply to the new select because the select's
3410 // 'logical' edges are incoming edges of the phi that is eliminated, not
3411 // the outgoing edges of PBI.
3412 if (HasWeights) {
3413 uint64_t PredCommon = PBIOp ? PredFalseWeight : PredTrueWeight;
3414 uint64_t PredOther = PBIOp ? PredTrueWeight : PredFalseWeight;
3415 uint64_t SuccCommon = BIOp ? SuccFalseWeight : SuccTrueWeight;
3416 uint64_t SuccOther = BIOp ? SuccTrueWeight : SuccFalseWeight;
3417 // The weight to PredCommonDest should be PredCommon * SuccTotal.
3418 // The weight to PredOtherDest should be PredOther * SuccCommon.
3419 uint64_t NewWeights[2] = {PredCommon * (SuccCommon + SuccOther),
3420 PredOther * SuccCommon};
3421
3422 FitWeights(NewWeights);
3423
3424 setBranchWeights(NV, NewWeights[0], NewWeights[1]);
3425 }
3426 }
3427 }
3428
3429 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "INTO: " << *PBI->getParent());
3430 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << *PBI->getParent()->getParent());
3431
3432 // This basic block is probably dead. We know it has at least
3433 // one fewer predecessor.
3434 return true;
3435}

3437// Simplifies a terminator by replacing it with a branch to TrueBB if Cond is
3438// true or to FalseBB if Cond is false.
3439// Takes care of updating the successors and removing the old terminator.
3440// Also makes sure not to introduce new successors by assuming that edges to
3441// non-successor TrueBBs and FalseBBs aren't reachable.
3442static bool SimplifyTerminatorOnSelect(Instruction *OldTerm, Value *Cond,
3443 BasicBlock *TrueBB, BasicBlock *FalseBB,
3444 uint32_t TrueWeight,
3445 uint32_t FalseWeight) {
3446 // Remove any superfluous successor edges from the CFG.
3447 // First, figure out which successors to preserve.
3448 // If TrueBB and FalseBB are equal, only try to preserve one copy of that
3449 // successor.
3450 BasicBlock *KeepEdge1 = TrueBB;
3451 BasicBlock *KeepEdge2 = TrueBB != FalseBB ? FalseBB : nullptr;
3452
3453 // Then remove the rest.
3454 for (BasicBlock *Succ : successors(OldTerm)) {
3455 // Make sure only to keep exactly one copy of each edge.
3456 if (Succ == KeepEdge1)
3457 KeepEdge1 = nullptr;
3458 else if (Succ == KeepEdge2)
3459 KeepEdge2 = nullptr;
3460 else
3461 Succ->removePredecessor(OldTerm->getParent(),
3462 /*KeepOneInputPHIs=*/true);
3463 }
3464
3465 IRBuilder<> Builder(OldTerm);
3466 Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(OldTerm->getDebugLoc());
3467
3468 // Insert an appropriate new terminator.
3469 if (!KeepEdge1 && !KeepEdge2) {
3470 if (TrueBB == FalseBB)
3471 // We were only looking for one successor, and it was present.
3472 // Create an unconditional branch to it.
3473 Builder.CreateBr(TrueBB);
3474 else {
3475 // We found both of the successors we were looking for.
3476 // Create a conditional branch sharing the condition of the select.
3477 BranchInst *NewBI = Builder.CreateCondBr(Cond, TrueBB, FalseBB);
3478 if (TrueWeight != FalseWeight)
3479 setBranchWeights(NewBI, TrueWeight, FalseWeight);
3480 }
3481 } else if (KeepEdge1 && (KeepEdge2 || TrueBB == FalseBB)) {
3482 // Neither of the selected blocks were successors, so this
3483 // terminator must be unreachable.
3484 new UnreachableInst(OldTerm->getContext(), OldTerm);
3485 } else {
3486 // One of the selected values was a successor, but the other wasn't.
3487 // Insert an unconditional branch to the one that was found;
3488 // the edge to the one that wasn't must be unreachable.
3489 if (!KeepEdge1)
3490 // Only TrueBB was found.
3491 Builder.CreateBr(TrueBB);
3492 else
3493 // Only FalseBB was found.
3494 Builder.CreateBr(FalseBB);
3495 }
3496
3497 EraseTerminatorAndDCECond(OldTerm);
3498 return true;
3499}

3501// Replaces
3502// (switch (select cond, X, Y)) on constant X, Y
3503// with a branch - conditional if X and Y lead to distinct BBs,
3504// unconditional otherwise.
3505static bool SimplifySwitchOnSelect(SwitchInst *SI, SelectInst *Select) {
3506 // Check for constant integer values in the select.
3507 ConstantInt *TrueVal = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Select->getTrueValue());
3508 ConstantInt *FalseVal = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Select->getFalseValue());
3509 if (!TrueVal || !FalseVal)
3510 return false;
3511
3512 // Find the relevant condition and destinations.
3513 Value *Condition = Select->getCondition();
3514 BasicBlock *TrueBB = SI->findCaseValue(TrueVal)->getCaseSuccessor();
3515 BasicBlock *FalseBB = SI->findCaseValue(FalseVal)->getCaseSuccessor();
3516
3517 // Get weight for TrueBB and FalseBB.
3518 uint32_t TrueWeight = 0, FalseWeight = 0;
3519 SmallVector<uint64_t, 8> Weights;
3520 bool HasWeights = HasBranchWeights(SI);
3521 if (HasWeights) {
3522 GetBranchWeights(SI, Weights);
3523 if (Weights.size() == 1 + SI->getNumCases()) {
3524 TrueWeight =
3525 (uint32_t)Weights[SI->findCaseValue(TrueVal)->getSuccessorIndex()];
3526 FalseWeight =
3527 (uint32_t)Weights[SI->findCaseValue(FalseVal)->getSuccessorIndex()];
3528 }
3529 }
3530
3531 // Perform the actual simplification.
3532 return SimplifyTerminatorOnSelect(SI, Condition, TrueBB, FalseBB, TrueWeight,
3533 FalseWeight);
3534}

3536// Replaces
3537// (indirectbr (select cond, blockaddress(@fn, BlockA),
3538// blockaddress(@fn, BlockB)))
3539// with
3540// (br cond, BlockA, BlockB).
3541static bool SimplifyIndirectBrOnSelect(IndirectBrInst *IBI, SelectInst *SI) {
3542 // Check that both operands of the select are block addresses.
3543 BlockAddress *TBA = dyn_cast<BlockAddress>(SI->getTrueValue());
3544 BlockAddress *FBA = dyn_cast<BlockAddress>(SI->getFalseValue());
3545 if (!TBA || !FBA)
3546 return false;
3547
3548 // Extract the actual blocks.
3549 BasicBlock *TrueBB = TBA->getBasicBlock();
3550 BasicBlock *FalseBB = FBA->getBasicBlock();
3551
3552 // Perform the actual simplification.
3553 return SimplifyTerminatorOnSelect(IBI, SI->getCondition(), TrueBB, FalseBB, 0,
3554 0);
3555}
3556
3557/// This is called when we find an icmp instruction
3558/// (a seteq/setne with a constant) as the only instruction in a
3559/// block that ends with an uncond branch. We are looking for a very specific
3560/// pattern that occurs when "A == 1 || A == 2 || A == 3" gets simplified. In
3561/// this case, we merge the first two "or's of icmp" into a switch, but then the
3562/// default value goes to an uncond block with a seteq in it, we get something
3563/// like:
3564///
3565/// switch i8 %A, label %DEFAULT [ i8 1, label %end i8 2, label %end ]
3566/// DEFAULT:
3567/// %tmp = icmp eq i8 %A, 92
3568/// br label %end
3569/// end:
3570/// ... = phi i1 [ true, %entry ], [ %tmp, %DEFAULT ], [ true, %entry ]
3571///
3572/// We prefer to split the edge to 'end' so that there is a true/false entry to
3573/// the PHI, merging the third icmp into the switch.
3574bool SimplifyCFGOpt::tryToSimplifyUncondBranchWithICmpInIt(
3575 ICmpInst *ICI, IRBuilder<> &Builder) {
3576 BasicBlock *BB = ICI->getParent();
3577
3578 // If the block has any PHIs in it or the icmp has multiple uses, it is too
3579 // complex.
3580 if (isa<PHINode>(BB->begin()) || !ICI->hasOneUse())
3581 return false;
3582
3583 Value *V = ICI->getOperand(0);
3584 ConstantInt *Cst = cast<ConstantInt>(ICI->getOperand(1));
3585
3586 // The pattern we're looking for is where our only predecessor is a switch on
3587 // 'V' and this block is the default case for the switch. In this case we can
3588 // fold the compared value into the switch to simplify things.
3589 BasicBlock *Pred = BB->getSinglePredecessor();
3590 if (!Pred || !isa<SwitchInst>(Pred->getTerminator()))
3591 return false;
3592
3593 SwitchInst *SI = cast<SwitchInst>(Pred->getTerminator());
3594 if (SI->getCondition() != V)
3595 return false;
3596
3597 // If BB is reachable on a non-default case, then we simply know the value of
3598 // V in this block. Substitute it and constant fold the icmp instruction
3599 // away.
3600 if (SI->getDefaultDest() != BB) {
3601 ConstantInt *VVal = SI->findCaseDest(BB);
3602 assert(VVal && "Should have a unique destination value");
3603 ICI->setOperand(0, VVal);
3604
3605 if (Value *V = SimplifyInstruction(ICI, {DL, ICI})) {
3606 ICI->replaceAllUsesWith(V);
3607 ICI->eraseFromParent();
3608 }
3609 // BB is now empty, so it is likely to simplify away.
3610 return requestResimplify();
3611 }
3612
3613 // Ok, the block is reachable from the default dest. If the constant we're
3614 // comparing exists in one of the other edges, then we can constant fold ICI
3615 // and zap it.
3616 if (SI->findCaseValue(Cst) != SI->case_default()) {
3617 Value *V;
3618 if (ICI->getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ)
3619 V = ConstantInt::getFalse(BB->getContext());
3620 else
3621 V = ConstantInt::getTrue(BB->getContext());
3622
3623 ICI->replaceAllUsesWith(V);
3624 ICI->eraseFromParent();
3625 // BB is now empty, so it is likely to simplify away.
3626 return requestResimplify();
3627 }
3628
3629 // The use of the icmp has to be in the 'end' block, by the only PHI node in
3630 // the block.
3631 BasicBlock *SuccBlock = BB->getTerminator()->getSuccessor(0);
3632 PHINode *PHIUse = dyn_cast<PHINode>(ICI->user_back());
3633 if (PHIUse == nullptr || PHIUse != &SuccBlock->front() ||
3634 isa<PHINode>(++BasicBlock::iterator(PHIUse)))
3635 return false;
3636
3637 // If the icmp is a SETEQ, then the default dest gets false, the new edge gets
3638 // true in the PHI.
3639 Constant *DefaultCst = ConstantInt::getTrue(BB->getContext());
3640 Constant *NewCst = ConstantInt::getFalse(BB->getContext());
3641
3642 if (ICI->getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ)
3643 std::swap(DefaultCst, NewCst);
3644
3645 // Replace ICI (which is used by the PHI for the default value) with true or
3646 // false depending on if it is EQ or NE.
3647 ICI->replaceAllUsesWith(DefaultCst);
3648 ICI->eraseFromParent();
3649
3650 // Okay, the switch goes to this block on a default value. Add an edge from
3651 // the switch to the merge point on the compared value.
3652 BasicBlock *NewBB =
3653 BasicBlock::Create(BB->getContext(), "switch.edge", BB->getParent(), BB);
3654 SmallVector<uint64_t, 8> Weights;
3655 bool HasWeights = HasBranchWeights(SI);
3656 if (HasWeights) {
3657 GetBranchWeights(SI, Weights);
3658 if (Weights.size() == 1 + SI->getNumCases()) {
3659 // Split weight for default case to case for "Cst".
3660 Weights[0] = (Weights[0] + 1) >> 1;
3661 Weights.push_back(Weights[0]);
3662
3663 SmallVector<uint32_t, 8> MDWeights(Weights.begin(), Weights.end());
3664 setBranchWeights(SI, MDWeights);
3665 }
3666 }
3667 SI->addCase(Cst, NewBB);
3668
3669 // NewBB branches to the phi block, add the uncond branch and the phi entry.
3670 Builder.SetInsertPoint(NewBB);
3671 Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(SI->getDebugLoc());
3672 Builder.CreateBr(SuccBlock);
3673 PHIUse->addIncoming(NewCst, NewBB);
3674 return true;
3675}
3676
3677/// The specified branch is a conditional branch.
3678/// Check to see if it is branching on an or/and chain of icmp instructions, and
3679/// fold it into a switch instruction if so.
3680static bool SimplifyBranchOnICmpChain(BranchInst *BI, IRBuilder<> &Builder,
3681 const DataLayout &DL) {
3682 Instruction *Cond = dyn_cast<Instruction>(BI->getCondition());
3683 if (!Cond)
3684 return false;
3685
3686 // Change br (X == 0 | X == 1), T, F into a switch instruction.
3687 // If this is a bunch of seteq's or'd together, or if it's a bunch of
3688 // 'setne's and'ed together, collect them.
3689
3690 // Try to gather values from a chain of and/or to be turned into a switch
3691 ConstantComparesGatherer ConstantCompare(Cond, DL);
3692 // Unpack the result
3693 SmallVectorImpl<ConstantInt *> &Values = ConstantCompare.Vals;
3694 Value *CompVal = ConstantCompare.CompValue;
3695 unsigned UsedICmps = ConstantCompare.UsedICmps;
3696 Value *ExtraCase = ConstantCompare.Extra;
3697
3698 // If we didn't have a multiply compared value, fail.
3699 if (!CompVal)
3700 return false;
3701
3702 // Avoid turning single icmps into a switch.
3703 if (UsedICmps <= 1)
3704 return false;
3705
3706 bool TrueWhenEqual = (Cond->getOpcode() == Instruction::Or);
3707
3708 // There might be duplicate constants in the list, which the switch
3709 // instruction can't handle, remove them now.
3710 array_pod_sort(Values.begin(), Values.end(), ConstantIntSortPredicate);
3711 Values.erase(std::unique(Values.begin(), Values.end()), Values.end());
3712
3713 // If Extra was used, we require at least two switch values to do the
3714 // transformation. A switch with one value is just a conditional branch.
3715 if (ExtraCase && Values.size() < 2)
3716 return false;
3717
3718 // TODO: Preserve branch weight metadata, similarly to how
3719 // FoldValueComparisonIntoPredecessors preserves it.
3720
3721 // Figure out which block is which destination.
3722 BasicBlock *DefaultBB = BI->getSuccessor(1);
3723 BasicBlock *EdgeBB = BI->getSuccessor(0);
3724 if (!TrueWhenEqual)
3725 std::swap(DefaultBB, EdgeBB);
3726
3727 BasicBlock *BB = BI->getParent();
3728
3729 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Converting 'icmp' chain with " << Values.size()
3730 << " cases into SWITCH. BB is:\n"
3731 << *BB);
3732
3733 // If there are any extra values that couldn't be folded into the switch
3734 // then we evaluate them with an explicit branch first. Split the block
3735 // right before the condbr to handle it.
3736 if (ExtraCase) {
3737 BasicBlock *NewBB =
3738 BB->splitBasicBlock(BI->getIterator(), "switch.early.test");
3739 // Remove the uncond branch added to the old block.
3740 Instruction *OldTI = BB->getTerminator();
3741 Builder.SetInsertPoint(OldTI);
3742
3743 if (TrueWhenEqual)
3744 Builder.CreateCondBr(ExtraCase, EdgeBB, NewBB);
3745 else
3746 Builder.CreateCondBr(ExtraCase, NewBB, EdgeBB);
3747
3748 OldTI->eraseFromParent();
3749
3750 // If there are PHI nodes in EdgeBB, then we need to add a new entry to them
3751 // for the edge we just added.
3752 AddPredecessorToBlock(EdgeBB, BB, NewBB);
3753
3754 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " ** 'icmp' chain unhandled condition: " << *ExtraCase
3755 << "\nEXTRABB = " << *BB);
3756 BB = NewBB;
3757 }
3758
3759 Builder.SetInsertPoint(BI);
3760 // Convert pointer to int before we switch.
3761 if (CompVal->getType()->isPointerTy()) {
3762 // For CHERI capabilities we want to compare the virtual address ->
3763 // call cap_address_get instead of ptrtoint which might be turned into
3764 // ctoptr in the hybrid ABI.
3765 if (isCheriPointer(CompVal->getType(), &DL)) {
3766 assert(cheri::isKnownUntaggedCapability(CompVal, &DL) && "This optimization should only be used with known untagged values");
3767 CompVal = Builder.CreateIntrinsic(Intrinsic::cheri_cap_address_get, DL.getIntPtrType(CompVal->getType()),
3768 CompVal, nullptr, "magicptr");
3769 } else {
3770 CompVal = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(
3771 CompVal, DL.getIntPtrType(CompVal->getType()), "magicptr");
3772 }
3773 }
3774
3775 // Create the new switch instruction now.
3776 SwitchInst *New = Builder.CreateSwitch(CompVal, DefaultBB, Values.size());
3777
3778 // Add all of the 'cases' to the switch instruction.
3779 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Values.size(); i != e; ++i)
3780 New->addCase(Values[i], EdgeBB);
3781
3782 // We added edges from PI to the EdgeBB. As such, if there were any
3783 // PHI nodes in EdgeBB, they need entries to be added corresponding to
3784 // the number of edges added.
3785 for (BasicBlock::iterator BBI = EdgeBB->begin(); isa<PHINode>(BBI); ++BBI) {
3786 PHINode *PN = cast<PHINode>(BBI);
3787 Value *InVal = PN->getIncomingValueForBlock(BB);
3788 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Values.size() - 1; i != e; ++i)
3789 PN->addIncoming(InVal, BB);
3790 }
3791
3792 // Erase the old branch instruction.
3793 EraseTerminatorAndDCECond(BI);
3794
3795 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " ** 'icmp' chain result is:\n" << *BB << '\n');
3796 return true;
3797}
