3799bool SimplifyCFGOpt::SimplifyResume(ResumeInst *RI, IRBuilder<> &Builder) {
3800 if (isa<PHINode>(RI->getValue()))
3801 return SimplifyCommonResume(RI);
3802 else if (isa<LandingPadInst>(RI->getParent()->getFirstNonPHI()) &&
3803 RI->getValue() == RI->getParent()->getFirstNonPHI())
3804 // The resume must unwind the exception that caused control to branch here.
3805 return SimplifySingleResume(RI);
3806
3807 return false;
3808}
3809
3810// Simplify resume that is shared by several landing pads (phi of landing pad).
3811bool SimplifyCFGOpt::SimplifyCommonResume(ResumeInst *RI) {
3812 BasicBlock *BB = RI->getParent();
3813
3814 // Check that there are no other instructions except for debug intrinsics
3815 // between the phi of landing pads (RI->getValue()) and resume instruction.
3816 BasicBlock::iterator I = cast<Instruction>(RI->getValue())->getIterator(),
3817 E = RI->getIterator();
3818 while (++I != E)
3819 if (!isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(I))
3820 return false;
3821
3822 SmallSetVector<BasicBlock *, 4> TrivialUnwindBlocks;
3823 auto *PhiLPInst = cast<PHINode>(RI->getValue());
3824
3825 // Check incoming blocks to see if any of them are trivial.
3826 for (unsigned Idx = 0, End = PhiLPInst->getNumIncomingValues(); Idx != End;
3827 Idx++) {
3828 auto *IncomingBB = PhiLPInst->getIncomingBlock(Idx);
3829 auto *IncomingValue = PhiLPInst->getIncomingValue(Idx);
3830
3831 // If the block has other successors, we can not delete it because
3832 // it has other dependents.
3833 if (IncomingBB->getUniqueSuccessor() != BB)
3834 continue;
3835
3836 auto *LandingPad = dyn_cast<LandingPadInst>(IncomingBB->getFirstNonPHI());
3837 // Not the landing pad that caused the control to branch here.
3838 if (IncomingValue != LandingPad)
3839 continue;
3840
3841 bool isTrivial = true;
3842
3843 I = IncomingBB->getFirstNonPHI()->getIterator();
3844 E = IncomingBB->getTerminator()->getIterator();
3845 while (++I != E)
3846 if (!isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(I)) {
3847 isTrivial = false;
3848 break;
3849 }
3850
3851 if (isTrivial)
3852 TrivialUnwindBlocks.insert(IncomingBB);
3853 }
3854
3855 // If no trivial unwind blocks, don't do any simplifications.
3856 if (TrivialUnwindBlocks.empty())
3857 return false;
3858
3859 // Turn all invokes that unwind here into calls.
3860 for (auto *TrivialBB : TrivialUnwindBlocks) {
3861 // Blocks that will be simplified should be removed from the phi node.
3862 // Note there could be multiple edges to the resume block, and we need
3863 // to remove them all.
3864 while (PhiLPInst->getBasicBlockIndex(TrivialBB) != -1)
3865 BB->removePredecessor(TrivialBB, true);
3866
3867 for (pred_iterator PI = pred_begin(TrivialBB), PE = pred_end(TrivialBB);
3868 PI != PE;) {
3869 BasicBlock *Pred = *PI++;
3870 removeUnwindEdge(Pred);
3871 }
3872
3873 // In each SimplifyCFG run, only the current processed block can be erased.
3874 // Otherwise, it will break the iteration of SimplifyCFG pass. So instead
3875 // of erasing TrivialBB, we only remove the branch to the common resume
3876 // block so that we can later erase the resume block since it has no
3877 // predecessors.
3878 TrivialBB->getTerminator()->eraseFromParent();
3879 new UnreachableInst(RI->getContext(), TrivialBB);
3880 }
3881
3882 // Delete the resume block if all its predecessors have been removed.
3883 if (pred_empty(BB))
3884 BB->eraseFromParent();
3885
3886 return !TrivialUnwindBlocks.empty();
3887}
3888
3889// Simplify resume that is only used by a single (non-phi) landing pad.
3890bool SimplifyCFGOpt::SimplifySingleResume(ResumeInst *RI) {
3891 BasicBlock *BB = RI->getParent();
3892 LandingPadInst *LPInst = dyn_cast<LandingPadInst>(BB->getFirstNonPHI());
3893 assert(RI->getValue() == LPInst &&
3894 "Resume must unwind the exception that caused control to here");
3895
3896 // Check that there are no other instructions except for debug intrinsics.
3897 BasicBlock::iterator I = LPInst->getIterator(), E = RI->getIterator();
3898 while (++I != E)
3899 if (!isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(I))
3900 return false;
3901
3902 // Turn all invokes that unwind here into calls and delete the basic block.
3903 for (pred_iterator PI = pred_begin(BB), PE = pred_end(BB); PI != PE;) {
3904 BasicBlock *Pred = *PI++;
3905 removeUnwindEdge(Pred);
3906 }
3907
3908 // The landingpad is now unreachable. Zap it.
3909 if (LoopHeaders)
3910 LoopHeaders->erase(BB);
3911 BB->eraseFromParent();
3912 return true;
3913}
3914
3915static bool removeEmptyCleanup(CleanupReturnInst *RI) {
3916 // If this is a trivial cleanup pad that executes no instructions, it can be
3917 // eliminated. If the cleanup pad continues to the caller, any predecessor
3918 // that is an EH pad will be updated to continue to the caller and any
3919 // predecessor that terminates with an invoke instruction will have its invoke
3920 // instruction converted to a call instruction. If the cleanup pad being
3921 // simplified does not continue to the caller, each predecessor will be
3922 // updated to continue to the unwind destination of the cleanup pad being
3923 // simplified.
3924 BasicBlock *BB = RI->getParent();
3925 CleanupPadInst *CPInst = RI->getCleanupPad();
3926 if (CPInst->getParent() != BB)
3927 // This isn't an empty cleanup.
3928 return false;
3929
3930 // We cannot kill the pad if it has multiple uses. This typically arises
3931 // from unreachable basic blocks.
3932 if (!CPInst->hasOneUse())
3933 return false;
3934
3935 // Check that there are no other instructions except for benign intrinsics.
3936 BasicBlock::iterator I = CPInst->getIterator(), E = RI->getIterator();
3937 while (++I != E) {
3938 auto *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(I);
3939 if (!II)
3940 return false;
3941
3942 Intrinsic::ID IntrinsicID = II->getIntrinsicID();
3943 switch (IntrinsicID) {
3944 case Intrinsic::dbg_declare:
3945 case Intrinsic::dbg_value:
3946 case Intrinsic::dbg_label:
3947 case Intrinsic::lifetime_end:
3948 break;
3949 default:
3950 return false;
3951 }
3952 }
3953
3954 // If the cleanup return we are simplifying unwinds to the caller, this will
3955 // set UnwindDest to nullptr.
3956 BasicBlock *UnwindDest = RI->getUnwindDest();
3957 Instruction *DestEHPad = UnwindDest ? UnwindDest->getFirstNonPHI() : nullptr;
3958
3959 // We're about to remove BB from the control flow. Before we do, sink any
3960 // PHINodes into the unwind destination. Doing this before changing the
3961 // control flow avoids some potentially slow checks, since we can currently
3962 // be certain that UnwindDest and BB have no common predecessors (since they
3963 // are both EH pads).
3964 if (UnwindDest) {
3965 // First, go through the PHI nodes in UnwindDest and update any nodes that
3966 // reference the block we are removing
3967 for (BasicBlock::iterator I = UnwindDest->begin(),
3968 IE = DestEHPad->getIterator();
3969 I != IE; ++I) {
3970 PHINode *DestPN = cast<PHINode>(I);
3971
3972 int Idx = DestPN->getBasicBlockIndex(BB);
3973 // Since BB unwinds to UnwindDest, it has to be in the PHI node.
3974 assert(Idx != -1);
3975 // This PHI node has an incoming value that corresponds to a control
3976 // path through the cleanup pad we are removing. If the incoming
3977 // value is in the cleanup pad, it must be a PHINode (because we
3978 // verified above that the block is otherwise empty). Otherwise, the
3979 // value is either a constant or a value that dominates the cleanup
3980 // pad being removed.
3981 //
3982 // Because BB and UnwindDest are both EH pads, all of their
3983 // predecessors must unwind to these blocks, and since no instruction
3984 // can have multiple unwind destinations, there will be no overlap in
3985 // incoming blocks between SrcPN and DestPN.
3986 Value *SrcVal = DestPN->getIncomingValue(Idx);
3987 PHINode *SrcPN = dyn_cast<PHINode>(SrcVal);
3988
3989 // Remove the entry for the block we are deleting.
3990 DestPN->removeIncomingValue(Idx, false);
3991
3992 if (SrcPN && SrcPN->getParent() == BB) {
3993 // If the incoming value was a PHI node in the cleanup pad we are
3994 // removing, we need to merge that PHI node's incoming values into
3995 // DestPN.
3996 for (unsigned SrcIdx = 0, SrcE = SrcPN->getNumIncomingValues();
3997 SrcIdx != SrcE; ++SrcIdx) {
3998 DestPN->addIncoming(SrcPN->getIncomingValue(SrcIdx),
3999 SrcPN->getIncomingBlock(SrcIdx));
4000 }
4001 } else {
4002 // Otherwise, the incoming value came from above BB and
4003 // so we can just reuse it. We must associate all of BB's
4004 // predecessors with this value.
4005 for (auto *pred : predecessors(BB)) {
4006 DestPN->addIncoming(SrcVal, pred);
4007 }
4008 }
4009 }
4010
4011 // Sink any remaining PHI nodes directly into UnwindDest.
4012 Instruction *InsertPt = DestEHPad;
4013 for (BasicBlock::iterator I = BB->begin(),
4014 IE = BB->getFirstNonPHI()->getIterator();
4015 I != IE;) {
4016 // The iterator must be incremented here because the instructions are
4017 // being moved to another block.
4018 PHINode *PN = cast<PHINode>(I++);
4019 if (PN->use_empty())
4020 // If the PHI node has no uses, just leave it. It will be erased
4021 // when we erase BB below.
4022 continue;
4023
4024 // Otherwise, sink this PHI node into UnwindDest.
4025 // Any predecessors to UnwindDest which are not already represented
4026 // must be back edges which inherit the value from the path through
4027 // BB. In this case, the PHI value must reference itself.
4028 for (auto *pred : predecessors(UnwindDest))
4029 if (pred != BB)
4030 PN->addIncoming(PN, pred);
4031 PN->moveBefore(InsertPt);
4032 }
4033 }
4034
4035 for (pred_iterator PI = pred_begin(BB), PE = pred_end(BB); PI != PE;) {
4036 // The iterator must be updated here because we are removing this pred.
4037 BasicBlock *PredBB = *PI++;
4038 if (UnwindDest == nullptr) {
4039 removeUnwindEdge(PredBB);
4040 } else {
4041 Instruction *TI = PredBB->getTerminator();
4042 TI->replaceUsesOfWith(BB, UnwindDest);
4043 }
4044 }
4045
4046 // The cleanup pad is now unreachable. Zap it.
4047 BB->eraseFromParent();
4048 return true;
4049}
4050
4051// Try to merge two cleanuppads together.
4052static bool mergeCleanupPad(CleanupReturnInst *RI) {
4053 // Skip any cleanuprets which unwind to caller, there is nothing to merge
4054 // with.
4055 BasicBlock *UnwindDest = RI->getUnwindDest();
4056 if (!UnwindDest)
4057 return false;
4058
4059 // This cleanupret isn't the only predecessor of this cleanuppad, it wouldn't
4060 // be safe to merge without code duplication.
4061 if (UnwindDest->getSinglePredecessor() != RI->getParent())
4062 return false;
4063
4064 // Verify that our cleanuppad's unwind destination is another cleanuppad.
4065 auto *SuccessorCleanupPad = dyn_cast<CleanupPadInst>(&UnwindDest->front());
4066 if (!SuccessorCleanupPad)
4067 return false;
4068
4069 CleanupPadInst *PredecessorCleanupPad = RI->getCleanupPad();
4070 // Replace any uses of the successor cleanupad with the predecessor pad
4071 // The only cleanuppad uses should be this cleanupret, it's cleanupret and
4072 // funclet bundle operands.
4073 SuccessorCleanupPad->replaceAllUsesWith(PredecessorCleanupPad);
4074 // Remove the old cleanuppad.
4075 SuccessorCleanupPad->eraseFromParent();
4076 // Now, we simply replace the cleanupret with a branch to the unwind
4077 // destination.
4078 BranchInst::Create(UnwindDest, RI->getParent());
4079 RI->eraseFromParent();
4080
4081 return true;
4082}
4083
4084bool SimplifyCFGOpt::SimplifyCleanupReturn(CleanupReturnInst *RI) {
4085 // It is possible to transiantly have an undef cleanuppad operand because we
4086 // have deleted some, but not all, dead blocks.
4087 // Eventually, this block will be deleted.
4088 if (isa<UndefValue>(RI->getOperand(0)))
4089 return false;
4090
4091 if (mergeCleanupPad(RI))
4092 return true;
4093
4094 if (removeEmptyCleanup(RI))
4095 return true;
4096
4097 return false;
4098}
4099
4100bool SimplifyCFGOpt::SimplifyReturn(ReturnInst *RI, IRBuilder<> &Builder) {
4101 BasicBlock *BB = RI->getParent();
4102 if (!BB->getFirstNonPHIOrDbg()->isTerminator())
4103 return false;
4104
4105 // Find predecessors that end with branches.
4106 SmallVector<BasicBlock *, 8> UncondBranchPreds;
4107 SmallVector<BranchInst *, 8> CondBranchPreds;
4108 for (pred_iterator PI = pred_begin(BB), E = pred_end(BB); PI != E; ++PI) {
4109 BasicBlock *P = *PI;
4110 Instruction *PTI = P->getTerminator();
4111 if (BranchInst *BI = dyn_cast<BranchInst>(PTI)) {
4112 if (BI->isUnconditional())
4113 UncondBranchPreds.push_back(P);
4114 else
4115 CondBranchPreds.push_back(BI);
4116 }
4117 }
4118
4119 // If we found some, do the transformation!
4120 if (!UncondBranchPreds.empty() && DupRet) {
4121 while (!UncondBranchPreds.empty()) {
4122 BasicBlock *Pred = UncondBranchPreds.pop_back_val();
4123 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "FOLDING: " << *BB
4124 << "INTO UNCOND BRANCH PRED: " << *Pred);
4125 (void)FoldReturnIntoUncondBranch(RI, BB, Pred);
4126 }
4127
4128 // If we eliminated all predecessors of the block, delete the block now.
4129 if (pred_empty(BB)) {
4130 // We know there are no successors, so just nuke the block.
4131 if (LoopHeaders)
4132 LoopHeaders->erase(BB);
4133 BB->eraseFromParent();
4134 }
4135
4136 return true;
4137 }
4138
4139 // Check out all of the conditional branches going to this return
4140 // instruction. If any of them just select between returns, change the
4141 // branch itself into a select/return pair.
4142 while (!CondBranchPreds.empty()) {
4143 BranchInst *BI = CondBranchPreds.pop_back_val();
4144
4145 // Check to see if the non-BB successor is also a return block.
4146 if (isa<ReturnInst>(BI->getSuccessor(0)->getTerminator()) &&
4147 isa<ReturnInst>(BI->getSuccessor(1)->getTerminator()) &&
4148 SimplifyCondBranchToTwoReturns(BI, Builder))
4149 return true;
4150 }
4151 return false;
4152}
4153
4154bool SimplifyCFGOpt::SimplifyUnreachable(UnreachableInst *UI) {
4155 BasicBlock *BB = UI->getParent();
4156
4157 bool Changed = false;
4158
4159 // If there are any instructions immediately before the unreachable that can
4160 // be removed, do so.
4161 while (UI->getIterator() != BB->begin()) {
4162 BasicBlock::iterator BBI = UI->getIterator();
4163 --BBI;
4164 // Do not delete instructions that can have side effects which might cause
4165 // the unreachable to not be reachable; specifically, calls and volatile
4166 // operations may have this effect.
4167 if (isa<CallInst>(BBI) && !isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(BBI))
4168 break;
4169
4170 if (BBI->mayHaveSideEffects()) {
4171 if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(BBI)) {
4172 if (SI->isVolatile())
4173 break;
4174 } else if (auto *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(BBI)) {
4175 if (LI->isVolatile())
4176 break;
4177 } else if (auto *RMWI = dyn_cast<AtomicRMWInst>(BBI)) {
4178 if (RMWI->isVolatile())
4179 break;
4180 } else if (auto *CXI = dyn_cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(BBI)) {
4181 if (CXI->isVolatile())
4182 break;
4183 } else if (isa<CatchPadInst>(BBI)) {
4184 // A catchpad may invoke exception object constructors and such, which
4185 // in some languages can be arbitrary code, so be conservative by
4186 // default.
4187 // For CoreCLR, it just involves a type test, so can be removed.
4188 if (classifyEHPersonality(BB->getParent()->getPersonalityFn()) !=
4189 EHPersonality::CoreCLR)
4190 break;
4191 } else if (!isa<FenceInst>(BBI) && !isa<VAArgInst>(BBI) &&
4192 !isa<LandingPadInst>(BBI)) {
4193 break;
4194 }
4195 // Note that deleting LandingPad's here is in fact okay, although it
4196 // involves a bit of subtle reasoning. If this inst is a LandingPad,
4197 // all the predecessors of this block will be the unwind edges of Invokes,
4198 // and we can therefore guarantee this block will be erased.
4199 }
4200
4201 // Delete this instruction (any uses are guaranteed to be dead)
4202 if (!BBI->use_empty())
4203 BBI->replaceAllUsesWith(UndefValue::get(BBI->getType()));
4204 BBI->eraseFromParent();
4205 Changed = true;
4206 }
4207
4208 // If the unreachable instruction is the first in the block, take a gander
4209 // at all of the predecessors of this instruction, and simplify them.
4210 if (&BB->front() != UI)
4211 return Changed;
4212
4213 SmallVector<BasicBlock *, 8> Preds(pred_begin(BB), pred_end(BB));
4214 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Preds.size(); i != e; ++i) {
4215 Instruction *TI = Preds[i]->getTerminator();
4216 IRBuilder<> Builder(TI);
4217 if (auto *BI = dyn_cast<BranchInst>(TI)) {
4218 if (BI->isUnconditional()) {
4219 if (BI->getSuccessor(0) == BB) {
4220 new UnreachableInst(TI->getContext(), TI);
4221 TI->eraseFromParent();
4222 Changed = true;
4223 }
4224 } else {
4225 Value* Cond = BI->getCondition();
4226 if (BI->getSuccessor(0) == BB) {
4227 Builder.CreateAssumption(Builder.CreateNot(Cond));
4228 Builder.CreateBr(BI->getSuccessor(1));
4229 EraseTerminatorAndDCECond(BI);
4230 } else if (BI->getSuccessor(1) == BB) {
4231 Builder.CreateAssumption(Cond);
4232 Builder.CreateBr(BI->getSuccessor(0));
4233 EraseTerminatorAndDCECond(BI);
4234 Changed = true;
4235 }
4236 }
4237 } else if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<SwitchInst>(TI)) {
4238 for (auto i = SI->case_begin(), e = SI->case_end(); i != e;) {
4239 if (i->getCaseSuccessor() != BB) {
4240 ++i;
4241 continue;
4242 }
4243 BB->removePredecessor(SI->getParent());
4244 i = SI->removeCase(i);
4245 e = SI->case_end();
4246 Changed = true;
4247 }
4248 } else if (auto *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(TI)) {
4249 if (II->getUnwindDest() == BB) {
4250 removeUnwindEdge(TI->getParent());
4251 Changed = true;
4252 }
4253 } else if (auto *CSI = dyn_cast<CatchSwitchInst>(TI)) {
4254 if (CSI->getUnwindDest() == BB) {
4255 removeUnwindEdge(TI->getParent());
4256 Changed = true;
4257 continue;
4258 }
4259
4260 for (CatchSwitchInst::handler_iterator I = CSI->handler_begin(),
4261 E = CSI->handler_end();
4262 I != E; ++I) {
4263 if (*I == BB) {
4264 CSI->removeHandler(I);
4265 --I;
4266 --E;
4267 Changed = true;
4268 }
4269 }
4270 if (CSI->getNumHandlers() == 0) {
4271 BasicBlock *CatchSwitchBB = CSI->getParent();
4272 if (CSI->hasUnwindDest()) {
4273 // Redirect preds to the unwind dest
4274 CatchSwitchBB->replaceAllUsesWith(CSI->getUnwindDest());
4275 } else {
4276 // Rewrite all preds to unwind to caller (or from invoke to call).
4277 SmallVector<BasicBlock *, 8> EHPreds(predecessors(CatchSwitchBB));
4278 for (BasicBlock *EHPred : EHPreds)
4279 removeUnwindEdge(EHPred);
4280 }
4281 // The catchswitch is no longer reachable.
4282 new UnreachableInst(CSI->getContext(), CSI);
4283 CSI->eraseFromParent();
4284 Changed = true;
4285 }
4286 } else if (isa<CleanupReturnInst>(TI)) {
4287 new UnreachableInst(TI->getContext(), TI);
4288 TI->eraseFromParent();
4289 Changed = true;
4290 }
4291 }
4292
4293 // If this block is now dead, remove it.
4294 if (pred_empty(BB) && BB != &BB->getParent()->getEntryBlock()) {
4295 // We know there are no successors, so just nuke the block.
4296 if (LoopHeaders)
4297 LoopHeaders->erase(BB);
4298 BB->eraseFromParent();
4299 return true;
4300 }
4301
4302 return Changed;
4303}
4304
4305static bool CasesAreContiguous(SmallVectorImpl<ConstantInt *> &Cases) {
4306 assert(Cases.size() >= 1);
4307
4308 array_pod_sort(Cases.begin(), Cases.end(), ConstantIntSortPredicate);
4309 for (size_t I = 1, E = Cases.size(); I != E; ++I) {
4310 if (Cases[I - 1]->getValue() != Cases[I]->getValue() + 1)
4311 return false;
4312 }
4313 return true;
4314}

4316/// Turn a switch with two reachable destinations into an integer range
4317/// comparison and branch.
4318static bool TurnSwitchRangeIntoICmp(SwitchInst *SI, IRBuilder<> &Builder) {
4319 assert(SI->getNumCases() > 1 && "Degenerate switch?");
4320
4321 bool HasDefault =
4322 !isa<UnreachableInst>(SI->getDefaultDest()->getFirstNonPHIOrDbg());
4323
4324 // Partition the cases into two sets with different destinations.
4325 BasicBlock *DestA = HasDefault ? SI->getDefaultDest() : nullptr;
4326 BasicBlock *DestB = nullptr;
4327 SmallVector<ConstantInt *, 16> CasesA;
4328 SmallVector<ConstantInt *, 16> CasesB;
4329
4330 for (auto Case : SI->cases()) {
4331 BasicBlock *Dest = Case.getCaseSuccessor();
4332 if (!DestA)
4333 DestA = Dest;
4334 if (Dest == DestA) {
4335 CasesA.push_back(Case.getCaseValue());
4336 continue;
4337 }
4338 if (!DestB)
4339 DestB = Dest;
4340 if (Dest == DestB) {
4341 CasesB.push_back(Case.getCaseValue());
4342 continue;
4343 }
4344 return false; // More than two destinations.
4345 }
4346
4347 assert(DestA && DestB &&
4348 "Single-destination switch should have been folded.");
4349 assert(DestA != DestB);
4350 assert(DestB != SI->getDefaultDest());
4351 assert(!CasesB.empty() && "There must be non-default cases.");
4352 assert(!CasesA.empty() || HasDefault);
4353
4354 // Figure out if one of the sets of cases form a contiguous range.
4355 SmallVectorImpl<ConstantInt *> *ContiguousCases = nullptr;
4356 BasicBlock *ContiguousDest = nullptr;
4357 BasicBlock *OtherDest = nullptr;
4358 if (!CasesA.empty() && CasesAreContiguous(CasesA)) {
4359 ContiguousCases = &CasesA;
4360 ContiguousDest = DestA;
4361 OtherDest = DestB;
4362 } else if (CasesAreContiguous(CasesB)) {
4363 ContiguousCases = &CasesB;
4364 ContiguousDest = DestB;
4365 OtherDest = DestA;
4366 } else
4367 return false;
4368
4369 // Start building the compare and branch.
4370
4371 Constant *Offset = ConstantExpr::getNeg(ContiguousCases->back());
4372 Constant *NumCases =
4373 ConstantInt::get(Offset->getType(), ContiguousCases->size());
4374
4375 Value *Sub = SI->getCondition();
4376 if (!Offset->isNullValue())
4377 Sub = Builder.CreateAdd(Sub, Offset, Sub->getName() + ".off");
4378
4379 Value *Cmp;
4380 // If NumCases overflowed, then all possible values jump to the successor.
4381 if (NumCases->isNullValue() && !ContiguousCases->empty())
4382 Cmp = ConstantInt::getTrue(SI->getContext());
4383 else
4384 Cmp = Builder.CreateICmpULT(Sub, NumCases, "switch");
4385 BranchInst *NewBI = Builder.CreateCondBr(Cmp, ContiguousDest, OtherDest);
4386
4387 // Update weight for the newly-created conditional branch.
4388 if (HasBranchWeights(SI)) {
4389 SmallVector<uint64_t, 8> Weights;
4390 GetBranchWeights(SI, Weights);
4391 if (Weights.size() == 1 + SI->getNumCases()) {
4392 uint64_t TrueWeight = 0;
4393 uint64_t FalseWeight = 0;
4394 for (size_t I = 0, E = Weights.size(); I != E; ++I) {
4395 if (SI->getSuccessor(I) == ContiguousDest)
4396 TrueWeight += Weights[I];
4397 else
4398 FalseWeight += Weights[I];
4399 }
4400 while (TrueWeight > UINT32_MAX || FalseWeight > UINT32_MAX) {
4401 TrueWeight /= 2;
4402 FalseWeight /= 2;
4403 }
4404 setBranchWeights(NewBI, TrueWeight, FalseWeight);
4405 }
4406 }
4407
4408 // Prune obsolete incoming values off the successors' PHI nodes.
4409 for (auto BBI = ContiguousDest->begin(); isa<PHINode>(BBI); ++BBI) {
4410 unsigned PreviousEdges = ContiguousCases->size();
4411 if (ContiguousDest == SI->getDefaultDest())
4412 ++PreviousEdges;
4413 for (unsigned I = 0, E = PreviousEdges - 1; I != E; ++I)
4414 cast<PHINode>(BBI)->removeIncomingValue(SI->getParent());
4415 }
4416 for (auto BBI = OtherDest->begin(); isa<PHINode>(BBI); ++BBI) {
4417 unsigned PreviousEdges = SI->getNumCases() - ContiguousCases->size();
4418 if (OtherDest == SI->getDefaultDest())
4419 ++PreviousEdges;
4420 for (unsigned I = 0, E = PreviousEdges - 1; I != E; ++I)
4421 cast<PHINode>(BBI)->removeIncomingValue(SI->getParent());
4422 }
4423
4424 // Drop the switch.
4425 SI->eraseFromParent();
4426
4427 return true;
4428}

4430/// Compute masked bits for the condition of a switch
4431/// and use it to remove dead cases.
4432static bool eliminateDeadSwitchCases(SwitchInst *SI, AssumptionCache *AC,
4433 const DataLayout &DL) {
4434 Value *Cond = SI->getCondition();
4435 unsigned Bits = Cond->getType()->getIntegerBitWidth();
4436 KnownBits Known = computeKnownBits(Cond, DL, 0, AC, SI);
4437
4438 // We can also eliminate cases by determining that their values are outside of
4439 // the limited range of the condition based on how many significant (non-sign)
4440 // bits are in the condition value.
4441 unsigned ExtraSignBits = ComputeNumSignBits(Cond, DL, 0, AC, SI) - 1;
4442 unsigned MaxSignificantBitsInCond = Bits - ExtraSignBits;
4443
4444 // Gather dead cases.
4445 SmallVector<ConstantInt *, 8> DeadCases;
4446 for (auto &Case : SI->cases()) {
4447 const APInt &CaseVal = Case.getCaseValue()->getValue();
4448 if (Known.Zero.intersects(CaseVal) || !Known.One.isSubsetOf(CaseVal) ||
4449 (CaseVal.getMinSignedBits() > MaxSignificantBitsInCond)) {
4450 DeadCases.push_back(Case.getCaseValue());
4451 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SimplifyCFG: switch case " << CaseVal
4452 << " is dead.\n");
4453 }
4454 }
4455
4456 // If we can prove that the cases must cover all possible values, the
4457 // default destination becomes dead and we can remove it. If we know some
4458 // of the bits in the value, we can use that to more precisely compute the
4459 // number of possible unique case values.
4460 bool HasDefault =
4461 !isa<UnreachableInst>(SI->getDefaultDest()->getFirstNonPHIOrDbg());
4462 const unsigned NumUnknownBits =
4463 Bits - (Known.Zero | Known.One).countPopulation();
4464 assert(NumUnknownBits <= Bits);
4465 if (HasDefault && DeadCases.empty() &&
4466 NumUnknownBits < 64 /* avoid overflow */ &&
4467 SI->getNumCases() == (1ULL << NumUnknownBits)) {
4468 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SimplifyCFG: switch default is dead.\n");
4469 BasicBlock *NewDefault =
4470 SplitBlockPredecessors(SI->getDefaultDest(), SI->getParent(), "");
4471 SI->setDefaultDest(&*NewDefault);
4472 SplitBlock(&*NewDefault, &NewDefault->front());
4473 auto *OldTI = NewDefault->getTerminator();
4474 new UnreachableInst(SI->getContext(), OldTI);
4475 EraseTerminatorAndDCECond(OldTI);
4476 return true;
4477 }
4478
4479 SmallVector<uint64_t, 8> Weights;
4480 bool HasWeight = HasBranchWeights(SI);
4481 if (HasWeight) {
4482 GetBranchWeights(SI, Weights);
4483 HasWeight = (Weights.size() == 1 + SI->getNumCases());
4484 }
4485
4486 // Remove dead cases from the switch.
4487 for (ConstantInt *DeadCase : DeadCases) {
4488 SwitchInst::CaseIt CaseI = SI->findCaseValue(DeadCase);
4489 assert(CaseI != SI->case_default() &&
4490 "Case was not found. Probably mistake in DeadCases forming.");
4491 if (HasWeight) {
4492 std::swap(Weights[CaseI->getCaseIndex() + 1], Weights.back());
4493 Weights.pop_back();
4494 }
4495
4496 // Prune unused values from PHI nodes.
4497 CaseI->getCaseSuccessor()->removePredecessor(SI->getParent());
4498 SI->removeCase(CaseI);
4499 }
4500 if (HasWeight && Weights.size() >= 2) {
4501 SmallVector<uint32_t, 8> MDWeights(Weights.begin(), Weights.end());
4502 setBranchWeights(SI, MDWeights);
4503 }
4504
4505 return !DeadCases.empty();
4506}
4507
4508/// If BB would be eligible for simplification by
4509/// TryToSimplifyUncondBranchFromEmptyBlock (i.e. it is empty and terminated
4510/// by an unconditional branch), look at the phi node for BB in the successor
4511/// block and see if the incoming value is equal to CaseValue. If so, return
4512/// the phi node, and set PhiIndex to BB's index in the phi node.
4513static PHINode *FindPHIForConditionForwarding(ConstantInt *CaseValue,
4514 BasicBlock *BB, int *PhiIndex) {
4515 if (BB->getFirstNonPHIOrDbg() != BB->getTerminator())
4516 return nullptr; // BB must be empty to be a candidate for simplification.
4517 if (!BB->getSinglePredecessor())
4518 return nullptr; // BB must be dominated by the switch.
4519
4520 BranchInst *Branch = dyn_cast<BranchInst>(BB->getTerminator());
4521 if (!Branch || !Branch->isUnconditional())
4522 return nullptr; // Terminator must be unconditional branch.
4523
4524 BasicBlock *Succ = Branch->getSuccessor(0);
4525
4526 for (PHINode &PHI : Succ->phis()) {
4527 int Idx = PHI.getBasicBlockIndex(BB);
4528 assert(Idx >= 0 && "PHI has no entry for predecessor?");
4529
4530 Value *InValue = PHI.getIncomingValue(Idx);
4531 if (InValue != CaseValue)
4532 continue;
4533
4534 *PhiIndex = Idx;
4535 return &PHI;
4536 }
4537
4538 return nullptr;
4539}
4540
4541/// Try to forward the condition of a switch instruction to a phi node
4542/// dominated by the switch, if that would mean that some of the destination
4543/// blocks of the switch can be folded away. Return true if a change is made.
4544static bool ForwardSwitchConditionToPHI(SwitchInst *SI) {
4545 using ForwardingNodesMap = DenseMap<PHINode *, SmallVector<int, 4>>;
4546
4547 ForwardingNodesMap ForwardingNodes;
4548 BasicBlock *SwitchBlock = SI->getParent();
4549 bool Changed = false;
4550 for (auto &Case : SI->cases()) {
4551 ConstantInt *CaseValue = Case.getCaseValue();
4552 BasicBlock *CaseDest = Case.getCaseSuccessor();
4553
4554 // Replace phi operands in successor blocks that are using the constant case
4555 // value rather than the switch condition variable:
4556 // switchbb:
4557 // switch i32 %x, label %default [
4558 // i32 17, label %succ
4559 // ...
4560 // succ:
4561 // %r = phi i32 ... [ 17, %switchbb ] ...
4562 // -->
4563 // %r = phi i32 ... [ %x, %switchbb ] ...
4564
4565 for (PHINode &Phi : CaseDest->phis()) {
4566 // This only works if there is exactly 1 incoming edge from the switch to
4567 // a phi. If there is >1, that means multiple cases of the switch map to 1
4568 // value in the phi, and that phi value is not the switch condition. Thus,
4569 // this transform would not make sense (the phi would be invalid because
4570 // a phi can't have different incoming values from the same block).
4571 int SwitchBBIdx = Phi.getBasicBlockIndex(SwitchBlock);
4572 if (Phi.getIncomingValue(SwitchBBIdx) == CaseValue &&
4573 count(Phi.blocks(), SwitchBlock) == 1) {
4574 Phi.setIncomingValue(SwitchBBIdx, SI->getCondition());
4575 Changed = true;
4576 }
4577 }
4578
4579 // Collect phi nodes that are indirectly using this switch's case constants.
4580 int PhiIdx;
4581 if (auto *Phi = FindPHIForConditionForwarding(CaseValue, CaseDest, &PhiIdx))
4582 ForwardingNodes[Phi].push_back(PhiIdx);
4583 }
4584
4585 for (auto &ForwardingNode : ForwardingNodes) {
4586 PHINode *Phi = ForwardingNode.first;
4587 SmallVectorImpl<int> &Indexes = ForwardingNode.second;
4588 if (Indexes.size() < 2)
4589 continue;
4590
4591 for (int Index : Indexes)
4592 Phi->setIncomingValue(Index, SI->getCondition());
4593 Changed = true;
4594 }
4595
4596 return Changed;
4597}

4599/// Return true if the backend will be able to handle
4600/// initializing an array of constants like C.
4601static bool ValidLookupTableConstant(Constant *C, const TargetTransformInfo &TTI) {
4602 if (C->isThreadDependent())
4603 return false;
4604 if (C->isDLLImportDependent())
4605 return false;
4606
4607 if (!isa<ConstantFP>(C) && !isa<ConstantInt>(C) &&
4608 !isa<ConstantPointerNull>(C) && !isa<GlobalValue>(C) &&
4609 !isa<UndefValue>(C) && !isa<ConstantExpr>(C))
4610 return false;
4611
4612 if (ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(C)) {
4613 if (!CE->isGEPWithNoNotionalOverIndexing())
4614 return false;
4615 if (!ValidLookupTableConstant(CE->getOperand(0), TTI))
4616 return false;
4617 }
4618
4619 if (!TTI.shouldBuildLookupTablesForConstant(C))
4620 return false;
4621
4622 return true;
4623}

4625/// If V is a Constant, return it. Otherwise, try to look up
4626/// its constant value in ConstantPool, returning 0 if it's not there.
4627static Constant *
4628LookupConstant(Value *V,
4629 const SmallDenseMap<Value *, Constant *> &ConstantPool) {
4630 if (Constant *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(V))
4631 return C;
4632 return ConstantPool.lookup(V);
4633}
4634
4635/// Try to fold instruction I into a constant. This works for
4636/// simple instructions such as binary operations where both operands are
4637/// constant or can be replaced by constants from the ConstantPool. Returns the
4638/// resulting constant on success, 0 otherwise.
4639static Constant *
4640ConstantFold(Instruction *I, const DataLayout &DL,
4641 const SmallDenseMap<Value *, Constant *> &ConstantPool) {
4642 if (SelectInst *Select = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(I)) {
4643 Constant *A = LookupConstant(Select->getCondition(), ConstantPool);
4644 if (!A)
4645 return nullptr;
4646 if (A->isAllOnesValue())
4647 return LookupConstant(Select->getTrueValue(), ConstantPool);
4648 if (A->isNullValue())
4649 return LookupConstant(Select->getFalseValue(), ConstantPool);
4650 return nullptr;
4651 }
4652
4653 SmallVector<Constant *, 4> COps;
4654 for (unsigned N = 0, E = I->getNumOperands(); N != E; ++N) {
4655 if (Constant *A = LookupConstant(I->getOperand(N), ConstantPool))
4656 COps.push_back(A);
4657 else
4658 return nullptr;
4659 }
4660
4661 if (CmpInst *Cmp = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(I)) {
4662 return ConstantFoldCompareInstOperands(Cmp->getPredicate(), COps[0],
4663 COps[1], DL);
4664 }
4665
4666 return ConstantFoldInstOperands(I, COps, DL);
4667}
4668
4669/// Try to determine the resulting constant values in phi nodes
4670/// at the common destination basic block, *CommonDest, for one of the case
4671/// destionations CaseDest corresponding to value CaseVal (0 for the default
4672/// case), of a switch instruction SI.
4673static bool
4674GetCaseResults(SwitchInst *SI, ConstantInt *CaseVal, BasicBlock *CaseDest,
4675 BasicBlock **CommonDest,
4676 SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<PHINode *, Constant *>> &Res,
4677 const DataLayout &DL, const TargetTransformInfo &TTI) {
4678 // The block from which we enter the common destination.
4679 BasicBlock *Pred = SI->getParent();
4680
4681 // If CaseDest is empty except for some side-effect free instructions through
4682 // which we can constant-propagate the CaseVal, continue to its successor.
4683 SmallDenseMap<Value *, Constant *> ConstantPool;
4684 ConstantPool.insert(std::make_pair(SI->getCondition(), CaseVal));
4685 for (Instruction &I :CaseDest->instructionsWithoutDebug()) {
4686 if (I.isTerminator()) {
4687 // If the terminator is a simple branch, continue to the next block.
4688 if (I.getNumSuccessors() != 1 || I.isExceptionalTerminator())
4689 return false;
4690 Pred = CaseDest;
4691 CaseDest = I.getSuccessor(0);
4692 } else if (Constant *C = ConstantFold(&I, DL, ConstantPool)) {
4693 // Instruction is side-effect free and constant.
4694
4695 // If the instruction has uses outside this block or a phi node slot for
4696 // the block, it is not safe to bypass the instruction since it would then
4697 // no longer dominate all its uses.
4698 for (auto &Use : I.uses()) {
4699 User *User = Use.getUser();
4700 if (Instruction *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(User))
4701 if (I->getParent() == CaseDest)
4702 continue;
4703 if (PHINode *Phi = dyn_cast<PHINode>(User))
4704 if (Phi->getIncomingBlock(Use) == CaseDest)
4705 continue;
4706 return false;
4707 }
4708
4709 ConstantPool.insert(std::make_pair(&I, C));
4710 } else {
4711 break;
4712 }
4713 }
4714
4715 // If we did not have a CommonDest before, use the current one.
4716 if (!*CommonDest)
4717 *CommonDest = CaseDest;
4718 // If the destination isn't the common one, abort.
4719 if (CaseDest != *CommonDest)
4720 return false;
4721
4722 // Get the values for this case from phi nodes in the destination block.
4723 for (PHINode &PHI : (*CommonDest)->phis()) {
4724 int Idx = PHI.getBasicBlockIndex(Pred);
4725 if (Idx == -1)
4726 continue;
4727
4728 Constant *ConstVal =
4729 LookupConstant(PHI.getIncomingValue(Idx), ConstantPool);
4730 if (!ConstVal)
4731 return false;
4732
4733 // Be conservative about which kinds of constants we support.
4734 if (!ValidLookupTableConstant(ConstVal, TTI))
4735 return false;
4736
4737 Res.push_back(std::make_pair(&PHI, ConstVal));
4738 }
4739
4740 return Res.size() > 0;
4741}

4743// Helper function used to add CaseVal to the list of cases that generate
4744// Result. Returns the updated number of cases that generate this result.
4745static uintptr_t MapCaseToResult(ConstantInt *CaseVal,
4746 SwitchCaseResultVectorTy &UniqueResults,
4747 Constant *Result) {
4748 for (auto &I : UniqueResults) {
4749 if (I.first == Result) {
4750 I.second.push_back(CaseVal);
4751 return I.second.size();
4752 }
4753 }
4754 UniqueResults.push_back(
4755 std::make_pair(Result, SmallVector<ConstantInt *, 4>(1, CaseVal)));
4756 return 1;
4757}
4758
4759// Helper function that initializes a map containing
4760// results for the PHI node of the common destination block for a switch
4761// instruction. Returns false if multiple PHI nodes have been found or if
4762// there is not a common destination block for the switch.
4763static bool
4764InitializeUniqueCases(SwitchInst *SI, PHINode *&PHI, BasicBlock *&CommonDest,
4765 SwitchCaseResultVectorTy &UniqueResults,
4766 Constant *&DefaultResult, const DataLayout &DL,
4767 const TargetTransformInfo &TTI,
4768 uintptr_t MaxUniqueResults, uintptr_t MaxCasesPerResult) {
4769 for (auto &I : SI->cases()) {
4770 ConstantInt *CaseVal = I.getCaseValue();
4771
4772 // Resulting value at phi nodes for this case value.
4773 SwitchCaseResultsTy Results;
4774 if (!GetCaseResults(SI, CaseVal, I.getCaseSuccessor(), &CommonDest, Results,
4775 DL, TTI))
4776 return false;
4777
4778 // Only one value per case is permitted.
4779 if (Results.size() > 1)
4780 return false;
4781
4782 // Add the case->result mapping to UniqueResults.
4783 const uintptr_t NumCasesForResult =
4784 MapCaseToResult(CaseVal, UniqueResults, Results.begin()->second);
4785
4786 // Early out if there are too many cases for this result.
4787 if (NumCasesForResult > MaxCasesPerResult)
4788 return false;
4789
4790 // Early out if there are too many unique results.
4791 if (UniqueResults.size() > MaxUniqueResults)
4792 return false;
4793
4794 // Check the PHI consistency.
4795 if (!PHI)
4796 PHI = Results[0].first;
4797 else if (PHI != Results[0].first)
4798 return false;
4799 }
4800 // Find the default result value.
4801 SmallVector<std::pair<PHINode *, Constant *>, 1> DefaultResults;
4802 BasicBlock *DefaultDest = SI->getDefaultDest();
4803 GetCaseResults(SI, nullptr, SI->getDefaultDest(), &CommonDest, DefaultResults,
4804 DL, TTI);
4805 // If the default value is not found abort unless the default destination
4806 // is unreachable.
4807 DefaultResult =
4808 DefaultResults.size() == 1 ? DefaultResults.begin()->second : nullptr;
4809 if ((!DefaultResult &&
4810 !isa<UnreachableInst>(DefaultDest->getFirstNonPHIOrDbg())))
4811 return false;
4812
4813 return true;
4814}
4815
4816// Helper function that checks if it is possible to transform a switch with only
4817// two cases (or two cases + default) that produces a result into a select.
4818// Example:
4819// switch (a) {
4820// case 10: %0 = icmp eq i32 %a, 10
4821// return 10; %1 = select i1 %0, i32 10, i32 4
4822// case 20: ----> %2 = icmp eq i32 %a, 20
4823// return 2; %3 = select i1 %2, i32 2, i32 %1
4824// default:
4825// return 4;
4826// }
4827static Value *ConvertTwoCaseSwitch(const SwitchCaseResultVectorTy &ResultVector,
4828 Constant *DefaultResult, Value *Condition,
4829 IRBuilder<> &Builder) {
4830 assert(ResultVector.size() == 2 &&
4831 "We should have exactly two unique results at this point");
4832 // If we are selecting between only two cases transform into a simple
4833 // select or a two-way select if default is possible.
4834 if (ResultVector[0].second.size() == 1 &&
4835 ResultVector[1].second.size() == 1) {
4836 ConstantInt *const FirstCase = ResultVector[0].second[0];
4837 ConstantInt *const SecondCase = ResultVector[1].second[0];
4838
4839 bool DefaultCanTrigger = DefaultResult;
4840 Value *SelectValue = ResultVector[1].first;
4841 if (DefaultCanTrigger) {
4842 Value *const ValueCompare =
4843 Builder.CreateICmpEQ(Condition, SecondCase, "switch.selectcmp");
4844 SelectValue = Builder.CreateSelect(ValueCompare, ResultVector[1].first,
4845 DefaultResult, "switch.select");
4846 }
4847 Value *const ValueCompare =
4848 Builder.CreateICmpEQ(Condition, FirstCase, "switch.selectcmp");
4849 return Builder.CreateSelect(ValueCompare, ResultVector[0].first,
4850 SelectValue, "switch.select");
4851 }
4852
4853 return nullptr;
4854}
4855
4856// Helper function to cleanup a switch instruction that has been converted into
4857// a select, fixing up PHI nodes and basic blocks.
4858static void RemoveSwitchAfterSelectConversion(SwitchInst *SI, PHINode *PHI,
4859 Value *SelectValue,
4860 IRBuilder<> &Builder) {
4861 BasicBlock *SelectBB = SI->getParent();
4862 while (PHI->getBasicBlockIndex(SelectBB) >= 0)
4863 PHI->removeIncomingValue(SelectBB);
4864 PHI->addIncoming(SelectValue, SelectBB);
4865
4866 Builder.CreateBr(PHI->getParent());
4867
4868 // Remove the switch.
4869 for (unsigned i = 0, e = SI->getNumSuccessors(); i < e; ++i) {
4870 BasicBlock *Succ = SI->getSuccessor(i);
4871
4872 if (Succ == PHI->getParent())
4873 continue;
4874 Succ->removePredecessor(SelectBB);
4875 }
4876 SI->eraseFromParent();
4877}
4878
4879/// If the switch is only used to initialize one or more
4880/// phi nodes in a common successor block with only two different
4881/// constant values, replace the switch with select.
4882static bool switchToSelect(SwitchInst *SI, IRBuilder<> &Builder,
4883 const DataLayout &DL,
4884 const TargetTransformInfo &TTI) {
4885 Value *const Cond = SI->getCondition();
4886 PHINode *PHI = nullptr;
4887 BasicBlock *CommonDest = nullptr;
4888 Constant *DefaultResult;
4889 SwitchCaseResultVectorTy UniqueResults;
4890 // Collect all the cases that will deliver the same value from the switch.
4891 if (!InitializeUniqueCases(SI, PHI, CommonDest, UniqueResults, DefaultResult,
4892 DL, TTI, 2, 1))
4893 return false;
4894 // Selects choose between maximum two values.
4895 if (UniqueResults.size() != 2)
4896 return false;
4897 assert(PHI != nullptr && "PHI for value select not found");
4898
4899 Builder.SetInsertPoint(SI);
4900 Value *SelectValue =
4901 ConvertTwoCaseSwitch(UniqueResults, DefaultResult, Cond, Builder);
4902 if (SelectValue) {
4903 RemoveSwitchAfterSelectConversion(SI, PHI, SelectValue, Builder);
4904 return true;
4905 }
4906 // The switch couldn't be converted into a select.
4907 return false;
4908}
