4910namespace {
4911
4912/// This class represents a lookup table that can be used to replace a switch.
4913class SwitchLookupTable {
4914public:
4915 /// Create a lookup table to use as a switch replacement with the contents
4916 /// of Values, using DefaultValue to fill any holes in the table.
4917 SwitchLookupTable(
4918 Module &M, uint64_t TableSize, ConstantInt *Offset,
4919 const SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<ConstantInt *, Constant *>> &Values,
4920 Constant *DefaultValue, const DataLayout &DL, const StringRef &FuncName);
4921
4922 /// Build instructions with Builder to retrieve the value at
4923 /// the position given by Index in the lookup table.
4924 Value *BuildLookup(Value *Index, IRBuilder<> &Builder);
4925
4926 /// Return true if a table with TableSize elements of
4927 /// type ElementType would fit in a target-legal register.
4928 static bool WouldFitInRegister(const DataLayout &DL, uint64_t TableSize,
4929 Type *ElementType);
4930
4931private:
4932 // Depending on the contents of the table, it can be represented in
4933 // different ways.
4934 enum {
4935 // For tables where each element contains the same value, we just have to
4936 // store that single value and return it for each lookup.
4937 SingleValueKind,
4938
4939 // For tables where there is a linear relationship between table index
4940 // and values. We calculate the result with a simple multiplication
4941 // and addition instead of a table lookup.
4942 LinearMapKind,
4943
4944 // For small tables with integer elements, we can pack them into a bitmap
4945 // that fits into a target-legal register. Values are retrieved by
4946 // shift and mask operations.
4947 BitMapKind,
4948
4949 // The table is stored as an array of values. Values are retrieved by load
4950 // instructions from the table.
4951 ArrayKind
4952 } Kind;
4953
4954 // For SingleValueKind, this is the single value.
4955 Constant *SingleValue = nullptr;
4956
4957 // For BitMapKind, this is the bitmap.
4958 ConstantInt *BitMap = nullptr;
4959 IntegerType *BitMapElementTy = nullptr;
4960
4961 // For LinearMapKind, these are the constants used to derive the value.
4962 ConstantInt *LinearOffset = nullptr;
4963 ConstantInt *LinearMultiplier = nullptr;
4964
4965 // For ArrayKind, this is the array.
4966 GlobalVariable *Array = nullptr;
4967};
4968
4969} // end anonymous namespace
4970
4971SwitchLookupTable::SwitchLookupTable(
4972 Module &M, uint64_t TableSize, ConstantInt *Offset,
4973 const SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<ConstantInt *, Constant *>> &Values,
4974 Constant *DefaultValue, const DataLayout &DL, const StringRef &FuncName) {
4975 assert(Values.size() && "Can't build lookup table without values!");
4976 assert(TableSize >= Values.size() && "Can't fit values in table!");
4977
4978 // If all values in the table are equal, this is that value.
4979 SingleValue = Values.begin()->second;
4980
4981 Type *ValueType = Values.begin()->second->getType();
4982
4983 // Build up the table contents.
4984 SmallVector<Constant *, 64> TableContents(TableSize);
4985 for (size_t I = 0, E = Values.size(); I != E; ++I) {
4986 ConstantInt *CaseVal = Values[I].first;
4987 Constant *CaseRes = Values[I].second;
4988 assert(CaseRes->getType() == ValueType);
4989
4990 uint64_t Idx = (CaseVal->getValue() - Offset->getValue()).getLimitedValue();
4991 TableContents[Idx] = CaseRes;
4992
4993 if (CaseRes != SingleValue)
4994 SingleValue = nullptr;
4995 }
4996
4997 // Fill in any holes in the table with the default result.
4998 if (Values.size() < TableSize) {
4999 assert(DefaultValue &&
5000 "Need a default value to fill the lookup table holes.");
5001 assert(DefaultValue->getType() == ValueType);
5002 for (uint64_t I = 0; I < TableSize; ++I) {
5003 if (!TableContents[I])
5004 TableContents[I] = DefaultValue;
5005 }
5006
5007 if (DefaultValue != SingleValue)
5008 SingleValue = nullptr;
5009 }
5010
5011 // If each element in the table contains the same value, we only need to store
5012 // that single value.
5013 if (SingleValue) {
5014 Kind = SingleValueKind;
5015 return;
5016 }
5017
5018 // Check if we can derive the value with a linear transformation from the
5019 // table index.
5020 if (isa<IntegerType>(ValueType)) {
5021 bool LinearMappingPossible = true;
5022 APInt PrevVal;
5023 APInt DistToPrev;
5024 assert(TableSize >= 2 && "Should be a SingleValue table.");
5025 // Check if there is the same distance between two consecutive values.
5026 for (uint64_t I = 0; I < TableSize; ++I) {
5027 ConstantInt *ConstVal = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(TableContents[I]);
5028 if (!ConstVal) {
5029 // This is an undef. We could deal with it, but undefs in lookup tables
5030 // are very seldom. It's probably not worth the additional complexity.
5031 LinearMappingPossible = false;
5032 break;
5033 }
5034 const APInt &Val = ConstVal->getValue();
5035 if (I != 0) {
5036 APInt Dist = Val - PrevVal;
5037 if (I == 1) {
5038 DistToPrev = Dist;
5039 } else if (Dist != DistToPrev) {
5040 LinearMappingPossible = false;
5041 break;
5042 }
5043 }
5044 PrevVal = Val;
5045 }
5046 if (LinearMappingPossible) {
5047 LinearOffset = cast<ConstantInt>(TableContents[0]);
5048 LinearMultiplier = ConstantInt::get(M.getContext(), DistToPrev);
5049 Kind = LinearMapKind;
5050 ++NumLinearMaps;
5051 return;
5052 }
5053 }
5054
5055 // If the type is integer and the table fits in a register, build a bitmap.
5056 if (WouldFitInRegister(DL, TableSize, ValueType)) {
5057 IntegerType *IT = cast<IntegerType>(ValueType);
5058 APInt TableInt(TableSize * IT->getBitWidth(), 0);
5059 for (uint64_t I = TableSize; I > 0; --I) {
5060 TableInt <<= IT->getBitWidth();
5061 // Insert values into the bitmap. Undef values are set to zero.
5062 if (!isa<UndefValue>(TableContents[I - 1])) {
5063 ConstantInt *Val = cast<ConstantInt>(TableContents[I - 1]);
5064 TableInt |= Val->getValue().zext(TableInt.getBitWidth());
5065 }
5066 }
5067 BitMap = ConstantInt::get(M.getContext(), TableInt);
5068 BitMapElementTy = IT;
5069 Kind = BitMapKind;
5070 ++NumBitMaps;
5071 return;
5072 }
5073
5074 // Store the table in an array.
5075 ArrayType *ArrayTy = ArrayType::get(ValueType, TableSize);
5076 Constant *Initializer = ConstantArray::get(ArrayTy, TableContents);
5077
5078 Array = new GlobalVariable(M, ArrayTy, /*constant=*/true,
5079 GlobalVariable::PrivateLinkage, Initializer,
5080 "switch.table." + FuncName);
5081 Array->setUnnamedAddr(GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
5082 // Set the alignment to that of an array items. We will be only loading one
5083 // value out of it.
5084 Array->setAlignment(DL.getPrefTypeAlignment(ValueType));
5085 Kind = ArrayKind;
5086}
5087
5088Value *SwitchLookupTable::BuildLookup(Value *Index, IRBuilder<> &Builder) {
5089 switch (Kind) {
5090 case SingleValueKind:
5091 return SingleValue;
5092 case LinearMapKind: {
5093 // Derive the result value from the input value.
5094 Value *Result = Builder.CreateIntCast(Index, LinearMultiplier->getType(),
5095 false, "switch.idx.cast");
5096 if (!LinearMultiplier->isOne())
5097 Result = Builder.CreateMul(Result, LinearMultiplier, "switch.idx.mult");
5098 if (!LinearOffset->isZero())
5099 Result = Builder.CreateAdd(Result, LinearOffset, "switch.offset");
5100 return Result;
5101 }
5102 case BitMapKind: {
5103 // Type of the bitmap (e.g. i59).
5104 IntegerType *MapTy = BitMap->getType();
5105
5106 // Cast Index to the same type as the bitmap.
5107 // Note: The Index is <= the number of elements in the table, so
5108 // truncating it to the width of the bitmask is safe.
5109 Value *ShiftAmt = Builder.CreateZExtOrTrunc(Index, MapTy, "switch.cast");
5110
5111 // Multiply the shift amount by the element width.
5112 ShiftAmt = Builder.CreateMul(
5113 ShiftAmt, ConstantInt::get(MapTy, BitMapElementTy->getBitWidth()),
5114 "switch.shiftamt");
5115
5116 // Shift down.
5117 Value *DownShifted =
5118 Builder.CreateLShr(BitMap, ShiftAmt, "switch.downshift");
5119 // Mask off.
5120 return Builder.CreateTrunc(DownShifted, BitMapElementTy, "switch.masked");
5121 }
5122 case ArrayKind: {
5123 // Make sure the table index will not overflow when treated as signed.
5124 IntegerType *IT = cast<IntegerType>(Index->getType());
5125 uint64_t TableSize =
5126 Array->getInitializer()->getType()->getArrayNumElements();
5127 if (TableSize > (1ULL << (IT->getBitWidth() - 1)))
5128 Index = Builder.CreateZExt(
5129 Index, IntegerType::get(IT->getContext(), IT->getBitWidth() + 1),
5130 "switch.tableidx.zext");
5131
5132 Value *GEPIndices[] = {Builder.getInt32(0), Index};
5133 Value *GEP = Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(Array->getValueType(), Array,
5134 GEPIndices, "switch.gep");
5135 return Builder.CreateLoad(
5136 cast<ArrayType>(Array->getValueType())->getElementType(), GEP,
5137 "switch.load");
5138 }
5139 }
5140 llvm_unreachable("Unknown lookup table kind!");
5141}
5142
5143bool SwitchLookupTable::WouldFitInRegister(const DataLayout &DL,
5144 uint64_t TableSize,
5145 Type *ElementType) {
5146 auto *IT = dyn_cast<IntegerType>(ElementType);
5147 if (!IT)
5148 return false;
5149 // FIXME: If the type is wider than it needs to be, e.g. i8 but all values
5150 // are <= 15, we could try to narrow the type.
5151
5152 // Avoid overflow, fitsInLegalInteger uses unsigned int for the width.
5153 if (TableSize >= UINT_MAX / IT->getBitWidth())
5154 return false;
5155 return DL.fitsInLegalInteger(TableSize * IT->getBitWidth());
5156}
5157
5158/// Determine whether a lookup table should be built for this switch, based on
5159/// the number of cases, size of the table, and the types of the results.
5160static bool
5161ShouldBuildLookupTable(SwitchInst *SI, uint64_t TableSize,
5162 const TargetTransformInfo &TTI, const DataLayout &DL,
5163 const SmallDenseMap<PHINode *, Type *> &ResultTypes) {
5164 if (SI->getNumCases() > TableSize || TableSize >= UINT64_MAX / 10)
5165 return false; // TableSize overflowed, or mul below might overflow.
5166
5167 bool AllTablesFitInRegister = true;
5168 bool HasIllegalType = false;
5169 for (const auto &I : ResultTypes) {
5170 Type *Ty = I.second;
5171
5172 // Saturate this flag to true.
5173 HasIllegalType = HasIllegalType || !TTI.isTypeLegal(Ty);
5174
5175 // Saturate this flag to false.
5176 AllTablesFitInRegister =
5177 AllTablesFitInRegister &&
5178 SwitchLookupTable::WouldFitInRegister(DL, TableSize, Ty);
5179
5180 // If both flags saturate, we're done. NOTE: This *only* works with
5181 // saturating flags, and all flags have to saturate first due to the
5182 // non-deterministic behavior of iterating over a dense map.
5183 if (HasIllegalType && !AllTablesFitInRegister)
5184 break;
5185 }
5186
5187 // If each table would fit in a register, we should build it anyway.
5188 if (AllTablesFitInRegister)
5189 return true;
5190
5191 // Don't build a table that doesn't fit in-register if it has illegal types.
5192 if (HasIllegalType)
5193 return false;
5194
5195 // The table density should be at least 40%. This is the same criterion as for
5196 // jump tables, see SelectionDAGBuilder::handleJTSwitchCase.
5197 // FIXME: Find the best cut-off.
5198 return SI->getNumCases() * 10 >= TableSize * 4;
5199}
5200
5201/// Try to reuse the switch table index compare. Following pattern:
5202/// \code
5203/// if (idx < tablesize)
5204/// r = table[idx]; // table does not contain default_value
5205/// else
5206/// r = default_value;
5207/// if (r != default_value)
5208/// ...
5209/// \endcode
5210/// Is optimized to:
5211/// \code
5212/// cond = idx < tablesize;
5213/// if (cond)
5214/// r = table[idx];
5215/// else
5216/// r = default_value;
5217/// if (cond)
5218/// ...
5219/// \endcode
5220/// Jump threading will then eliminate the second if(cond).
5221static void reuseTableCompare(
5222 User *PhiUser, BasicBlock *PhiBlock, BranchInst *RangeCheckBranch,
5223 Constant *DefaultValue,
5224 const SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<ConstantInt *, Constant *>> &Values) {
5225 ICmpInst *CmpInst = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(PhiUser);
5226 if (!CmpInst)
5227 return;
5228
5229 // We require that the compare is in the same block as the phi so that jump
5230 // threading can do its work afterwards.
5231 if (CmpInst->getParent() != PhiBlock)
5232 return;
5233
5234 Constant *CmpOp1 = dyn_cast<Constant>(CmpInst->getOperand(1));
5235 if (!CmpOp1)
5236 return;
5237
5238 Value *RangeCmp = RangeCheckBranch->getCondition();
5239 Constant *TrueConst = ConstantInt::getTrue(RangeCmp->getType());
5240 Constant *FalseConst = ConstantInt::getFalse(RangeCmp->getType());
5241
5242 // Check if the compare with the default value is constant true or false.
5243 Constant *DefaultConst = ConstantExpr::getICmp(CmpInst->getPredicate(),
5244 DefaultValue, CmpOp1, true);
5245 if (DefaultConst != TrueConst && DefaultConst != FalseConst)
5246 return;
5247
5248 // Check if the compare with the case values is distinct from the default
5249 // compare result.
5250 for (auto ValuePair : Values) {
5251 Constant *CaseConst = ConstantExpr::getICmp(CmpInst->getPredicate(),
5252 ValuePair.second, CmpOp1, true);
5253 if (!CaseConst || CaseConst == DefaultConst || isa<UndefValue>(CaseConst))
5254 return;
5255 assert((CaseConst == TrueConst || CaseConst == FalseConst) &&
5256 "Expect true or false as compare result.");
5257 }
5258
5259 // Check if the branch instruction dominates the phi node. It's a simple
5260 // dominance check, but sufficient for our needs.
5261 // Although this check is invariant in the calling loops, it's better to do it
5262 // at this late stage. Practically we do it at most once for a switch.
5263 BasicBlock *BranchBlock = RangeCheckBranch->getParent();
5264 for (auto PI = pred_begin(PhiBlock), E = pred_end(PhiBlock); PI != E; ++PI) {
5265 BasicBlock *Pred = *PI;
5266 if (Pred != BranchBlock && Pred->getUniquePredecessor() != BranchBlock)
5267 return;
5268 }
5269
5270 if (DefaultConst == FalseConst) {
5271 // The compare yields the same result. We can replace it.
5272 CmpInst->replaceAllUsesWith(RangeCmp);
5273 ++NumTableCmpReuses;
5274 } else {
5275 // The compare yields the same result, just inverted. We can replace it.
5276 Value *InvertedTableCmp = BinaryOperator::CreateXor(
5277 RangeCmp, ConstantInt::get(RangeCmp->getType(), 1), "inverted.cmp",
5278 RangeCheckBranch);
5279 CmpInst->replaceAllUsesWith(InvertedTableCmp);
5280 ++NumTableCmpReuses;
5281 }
5282}
5283
5284/// If the switch is only used to initialize one or more phi nodes in a common
5285/// successor block with different constant values, replace the switch with
5286/// lookup tables.
5287static bool SwitchToLookupTable(SwitchInst *SI, IRBuilder<> &Builder,
5288 const DataLayout &DL,
5289 const TargetTransformInfo &TTI) {
5290 assert(SI->getNumCases() > 1 && "Degenerate switch?");
5291
5292 Function *Fn = SI->getParent()->getParent();
5293 // Only build lookup table when we have a target that supports it or the
5294 // attribute is not set.
5295 if (!TTI.shouldBuildLookupTables() ||
5296 (Fn->getFnAttribute("no-jump-tables").getValueAsString() == "true"))
5297 return false;
5298
5299 // FIXME: This is a work-around for the lack of linker support in CHERI: We
5300 // can't construct jump tables if we're using the pure-cap ABI because we
5301 // don't have a way of statically generating all of the constant GEPs to jump
5302 // table entries.
5303 // XXXAR: this check does not seem to be working as we are still generating
5304 // jump tables for the purecap ABI? Possibly caused by DL->setAllocaAS(0); in
5305 // CheriSandboxABI.cpp?
5306 if (DL.getAllocaAddrSpace() != 0)
5307 return false;
5308
5309 // FIXME: If the switch is too sparse for a lookup table, perhaps we could
5310 // split off a dense part and build a lookup table for that.
5311
5312 // FIXME: This creates arrays of GEPs to constant strings, which means each
5313 // GEP needs a runtime relocation in PIC code. We should just build one big
5314 // string and lookup indices into that.
5315
5316 // Ignore switches with less than three cases. Lookup tables will not make
5317 // them faster, so we don't analyze them.
5318 if (SI->getNumCases() < 3)
5319 return false;
5320
5321 // Figure out the corresponding result for each case value and phi node in the
5322 // common destination, as well as the min and max case values.
5323 assert(!empty(SI->cases()));
5324 SwitchInst::CaseIt CI = SI->case_begin();
5325 ConstantInt *MinCaseVal = CI->getCaseValue();
5326 ConstantInt *MaxCaseVal = CI->getCaseValue();
5327
5328 BasicBlock *CommonDest = nullptr;
5329
5330 using ResultListTy = SmallVector<std::pair<ConstantInt *, Constant *>, 4>;
5331 SmallDenseMap<PHINode *, ResultListTy> ResultLists;
5332
5333 SmallDenseMap<PHINode *, Constant *> DefaultResults;
5334 SmallDenseMap<PHINode *, Type *> ResultTypes;
5335 SmallVector<PHINode *, 4> PHIs;
5336
5337 for (SwitchInst::CaseIt E = SI->case_end(); CI != E; ++CI) {
5338 ConstantInt *CaseVal = CI->getCaseValue();
5339 if (CaseVal->getValue().slt(MinCaseVal->getValue()))
5340 MinCaseVal = CaseVal;
5341 if (CaseVal->getValue().sgt(MaxCaseVal->getValue()))
5342 MaxCaseVal = CaseVal;
5343
5344 // Resulting value at phi nodes for this case value.
5345 using ResultsTy = SmallVector<std::pair<PHINode *, Constant *>, 4>;
5346 ResultsTy Results;
5347 if (!GetCaseResults(SI, CaseVal, CI->getCaseSuccessor(), &CommonDest,
5348 Results, DL, TTI))
5349 return false;
5350
5351 // Append the result from this case to the list for each phi.
5352 for (const auto &I : Results) {
5353 PHINode *PHI = I.first;
5354 Constant *Value = I.second;
5355 if (!ResultLists.count(PHI))
5356 PHIs.push_back(PHI);
5357 ResultLists[PHI].push_back(std::make_pair(CaseVal, Value));
5358 }
5359 }
5360
5361 // Keep track of the result types.
5362 for (PHINode *PHI : PHIs) {
5363 ResultTypes[PHI] = ResultLists[PHI][0].second->getType();
5364 }
5365
5366 uint64_t NumResults = ResultLists[PHIs[0]].size();
5367 APInt RangeSpread = MaxCaseVal->getValue() - MinCaseVal->getValue();
5368 uint64_t TableSize = RangeSpread.getLimitedValue() + 1;
5369 bool TableHasHoles = (NumResults < TableSize);
5370
5371 // If the table has holes, we need a constant result for the default case
5372 // or a bitmask that fits in a register.
5373 SmallVector<std::pair<PHINode *, Constant *>, 4> DefaultResultsList;
5374 bool HasDefaultResults =
5375 GetCaseResults(SI, nullptr, SI->getDefaultDest(), &CommonDest,
5376 DefaultResultsList, DL, TTI);
5377
5378 bool NeedMask = (TableHasHoles && !HasDefaultResults);
5379 if (NeedMask) {
5380 // As an extra penalty for the validity test we require more cases.
5381 if (SI->getNumCases() < 4) // FIXME: Find best threshold value (benchmark).
5382 return false;
5383 if (!DL.fitsInLegalInteger(TableSize))
5384 return false;
5385 }
5386
5387 for (const auto &I : DefaultResultsList) {
5388 PHINode *PHI = I.first;
5389 Constant *Result = I.second;
5390 DefaultResults[PHI] = Result;
5391 }
5392
5393 if (!ShouldBuildLookupTable(SI, TableSize, TTI, DL, ResultTypes))
5394 return false;
5395
5396 // Create the BB that does the lookups.
5397 Module &Mod = *CommonDest->getParent()->getParent();
5398 BasicBlock *LookupBB = BasicBlock::Create(
5399 Mod.getContext(), "switch.lookup", CommonDest->getParent(), CommonDest);
5400
5401 // Compute the table index value.
5402 Builder.SetInsertPoint(SI);
5403 Value *TableIndex;
5404 if (MinCaseVal->isNullValue())
5405 TableIndex = SI->getCondition();
5406 else
5407 TableIndex = Builder.CreateSub(SI->getCondition(), MinCaseVal,
5408 "switch.tableidx");
5409
5410 // Compute the maximum table size representable by the integer type we are
5411 // switching upon.
5412 unsigned CaseSize = MinCaseVal->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
5413 uint64_t MaxTableSize = CaseSize > 63 ? UINT64_MAX : 1ULL << CaseSize;
5414 assert(MaxTableSize >= TableSize &&
5415 "It is impossible for a switch to have more entries than the max "
5416 "representable value of its input integer type's size.");
5417
5418 // If the default destination is unreachable, or if the lookup table covers
5419 // all values of the conditional variable, branch directly to the lookup table
5420 // BB. Otherwise, check that the condition is within the case range.
5421 const bool DefaultIsReachable =
5422 !isa<UnreachableInst>(SI->getDefaultDest()->getFirstNonPHIOrDbg());
5423 const bool GeneratingCoveredLookupTable = (MaxTableSize == TableSize);
5424 BranchInst *RangeCheckBranch = nullptr;
5425
5426 if (!DefaultIsReachable || GeneratingCoveredLookupTable) {
5427 Builder.CreateBr(LookupBB);
5428 // Note: We call removeProdecessor later since we need to be able to get the
5429 // PHI value for the default case in case we're using a bit mask.
5430 } else {
5431 Value *Cmp = Builder.CreateICmpULT(
5432 TableIndex, ConstantInt::get(MinCaseVal->getType(), TableSize));
5433 RangeCheckBranch =
5434 Builder.CreateCondBr(Cmp, LookupBB, SI->getDefaultDest());
5435 }
5436
5437 // Populate the BB that does the lookups.
5438 Builder.SetInsertPoint(LookupBB);
5439
5440 if (NeedMask) {
5441 // Before doing the lookup, we do the hole check. The LookupBB is therefore
5442 // re-purposed to do the hole check, and we create a new LookupBB.
5443 BasicBlock *MaskBB = LookupBB;
5444 MaskBB->setName("switch.hole_check");
5445 LookupBB = BasicBlock::Create(Mod.getContext(), "switch.lookup",
5446 CommonDest->getParent(), CommonDest);
5447
5448 // Make the mask's bitwidth at least 8-bit and a power-of-2 to avoid
5449 // unnecessary illegal types.
5450 uint64_t TableSizePowOf2 = NextPowerOf2(std::max(7ULL, TableSize - 1ULL));
5451 APInt MaskInt(TableSizePowOf2, 0);
5452 APInt One(TableSizePowOf2, 1);
5453 // Build bitmask; fill in a 1 bit for every case.
5454 const ResultListTy &ResultList = ResultLists[PHIs[0]];
5455 for (size_t I = 0, E = ResultList.size(); I != E; ++I) {
5456 uint64_t Idx = (ResultList[I].first->getValue() - MinCaseVal->getValue())
5457 .getLimitedValue();
5458 MaskInt |= One << Idx;
5459 }
5460 ConstantInt *TableMask = ConstantInt::get(Mod.getContext(), MaskInt);
5461
5462 // Get the TableIndex'th bit of the bitmask.
5463 // If this bit is 0 (meaning hole) jump to the default destination,
5464 // else continue with table lookup.
5465 IntegerType *MapTy = TableMask->getType();
5466 Value *MaskIndex =
5467 Builder.CreateZExtOrTrunc(TableIndex, MapTy, "switch.maskindex");
5468 Value *Shifted = Builder.CreateLShr(TableMask, MaskIndex, "switch.shifted");
5469 Value *LoBit = Builder.CreateTrunc(
5470 Shifted, Type::getInt1Ty(Mod.getContext()), "switch.lobit");
5471 Builder.CreateCondBr(LoBit, LookupBB, SI->getDefaultDest());
5472
5473 Builder.SetInsertPoint(LookupBB);
5474 AddPredecessorToBlock(SI->getDefaultDest(), MaskBB, SI->getParent());
5475 }
5476
5477 if (!DefaultIsReachable || GeneratingCoveredLookupTable) {
5478 // We cached PHINodes in PHIs. To avoid accessing deleted PHINodes later,
5479 // do not delete PHINodes here.
5480 SI->getDefaultDest()->removePredecessor(SI->getParent(),
5481 /*KeepOneInputPHIs=*/true);
5482 }
5483
5484 bool ReturnedEarly = false;
5485 for (PHINode *PHI : PHIs) {
5486 const ResultListTy &ResultList = ResultLists[PHI];
5487
5488 // If using a bitmask, use any value to fill the lookup table holes.
5489 Constant *DV = NeedMask ? ResultLists[PHI][0].second : DefaultResults[PHI];
5490 StringRef FuncName = Fn->getName();
5491 SwitchLookupTable Table(Mod, TableSize, MinCaseVal, ResultList, DV, DL,
5492 FuncName);
5493
5494 Value *Result = Table.BuildLookup(TableIndex, Builder);
5495
5496 // If the result is used to return immediately from the function, we want to
5497 // do that right here.
5498 if (PHI->hasOneUse() && isa<ReturnInst>(*PHI->user_begin()) &&
5499 PHI->user_back() == CommonDest->getFirstNonPHIOrDbg()) {
5500 Builder.CreateRet(Result);
5501 ReturnedEarly = true;
5502 break;
5503 }
5504
5505 // Do a small peephole optimization: re-use the switch table compare if
5506 // possible.
5507 if (!TableHasHoles && HasDefaultResults && RangeCheckBranch) {
5508 BasicBlock *PhiBlock = PHI->getParent();
5509 // Search for compare instructions which use the phi.
5510 for (auto *User : PHI->users()) {
5511 reuseTableCompare(User, PhiBlock, RangeCheckBranch, DV, ResultList);
5512 }
5513 }
5514
5515 PHI->addIncoming(Result, LookupBB);
5516 }
5517
5518 if (!ReturnedEarly)
5519 Builder.CreateBr(CommonDest);
5520
5521 // Remove the switch.
5522 for (unsigned i = 0, e = SI->getNumSuccessors(); i < e; ++i) {
5523 BasicBlock *Succ = SI->getSuccessor(i);
5524
5525 if (Succ == SI->getDefaultDest())
5526 continue;
5527 Succ->removePredecessor(SI->getParent());
5528 }
5529 SI->eraseFromParent();
5530
5531 ++NumLookupTables;
5532 if (NeedMask)
5533 ++NumLookupTablesHoles;
5534 return true;
5535}
5536
5537static bool isSwitchDense(ArrayRef<int64_t> Values) {
5538 // See also SelectionDAGBuilder::isDense(), which this function was based on.
5539 uint64_t Diff = (uint64_t)Values.back() - (uint64_t)Values.front();
5540 uint64_t Range = Diff + 1;
5541 uint64_t NumCases = Values.size();
5542 // 40% is the default density for building a jump table in optsize/minsize mode.
5543 uint64_t MinDensity = 40;
5544
5545 return NumCases * 100 >= Range * MinDensity;
5546}
5547
5548/// Try to transform a switch that has "holes" in it to a contiguous sequence
5549/// of cases.
5550///
5551/// A switch such as: switch(i) {case 5: case 9: case 13: case 17:} can be
5552/// range-reduced to: switch ((i-5) / 4) {case 0: case 1: case 2: case 3:}.
5553///
5554/// This converts a sparse switch into a dense switch which allows better
5555/// lowering and could also allow transforming into a lookup table.
5556static bool ReduceSwitchRange(SwitchInst *SI, IRBuilder<> &Builder,
5557 const DataLayout &DL,
5558 const TargetTransformInfo &TTI) {
5559 auto *CondTy = cast<IntegerType>(SI->getCondition()->getType());
5560 if (CondTy->getIntegerBitWidth() > 64 ||
5561 !DL.fitsInLegalInteger(CondTy->getIntegerBitWidth()))
5562 return false;
5563 // Only bother with this optimization if there are more than 3 switch cases;
5564 // SDAG will only bother creating jump tables for 4 or more cases.
5565 if (SI->getNumCases() < 4)
5566 return false;
5567
5568 // This transform is agnostic to the signedness of the input or case values. We
5569 // can treat the case values as signed or unsigned. We can optimize more common
5570 // cases such as a sequence crossing zero {-4,0,4,8} if we interpret case values
5571 // as signed.
5572 SmallVector<int64_t,4> Values;
5573 for (auto &C : SI->cases())
5574 Values.push_back(C.getCaseValue()->getValue().getSExtValue());
5575 llvm::sort(Values);
5576
5577 // If the switch is already dense, there's nothing useful to do here.
5578 if (isSwitchDense(Values))
5579 return false;
5580
5581 // First, transform the values such that they start at zero and ascend.
5582 int64_t Base = Values[0];
5583 for (auto &V : Values)
5584 V -= (uint64_t)(Base);
5585
5586 // Now we have signed numbers that have been shifted so that, given enough
5587 // precision, there are no negative values. Since the rest of the transform
5588 // is bitwise only, we switch now to an unsigned representation.
5589 uint64_t GCD = 0;
5590 for (auto &V : Values)
5591 GCD = GreatestCommonDivisor64(GCD, (uint64_t)V);
5592
5593 // This transform can be done speculatively because it is so cheap - it results
5594 // in a single rotate operation being inserted. This can only happen if the
5595 // factor extracted is a power of 2.
5596 // FIXME: If the GCD is an odd number we can multiply by the multiplicative
5597 // inverse of GCD and then perform this transform.
5598 // FIXME: It's possible that optimizing a switch on powers of two might also
5599 // be beneficial - flag values are often powers of two and we could use a CLZ
5600 // as the key function.
5601 if (GCD <= 1 || !isPowerOf2_64(GCD))
5602 // No common divisor found or too expensive to compute key function.
5603 return false;
5604
5605 unsigned Shift = Log2_64(GCD);
5606 for (auto &V : Values)
5607 V = (int64_t)((uint64_t)V >> Shift);
5608
5609 if (!isSwitchDense(Values))
5610 // Transform didn't create a dense switch.
5611 return false;
5612
5613 // The obvious transform is to shift the switch condition right and emit a
5614 // check that the condition actually cleanly divided by GCD, i.e.
5615 // C & (1 << Shift - 1) == 0
5616 // inserting a new CFG edge to handle the case where it didn't divide cleanly.
5617 //
5618 // A cheaper way of doing this is a simple ROTR(C, Shift). This performs the
5619 // shift and puts the shifted-off bits in the uppermost bits. If any of these
5620 // are nonzero then the switch condition will be very large and will hit the
5621 // default case.
5622
5623 auto *Ty = cast<IntegerType>(SI->getCondition()->getType());
5624 Builder.SetInsertPoint(SI);
5625 auto *ShiftC = ConstantInt::get(Ty, Shift);
5626 auto *Sub = Builder.CreateSub(SI->getCondition(), ConstantInt::get(Ty, Base));
5627 auto *LShr = Builder.CreateLShr(Sub, ShiftC);
5628 auto *Shl = Builder.CreateShl(Sub, Ty->getBitWidth() - Shift);
5629 auto *Rot = Builder.CreateOr(LShr, Shl);
5630 SI->replaceUsesOfWith(SI->getCondition(), Rot);
5631
5632 for (auto Case : SI->cases()) {
5633 auto *Orig = Case.getCaseValue();
5634 auto Sub = Orig->getValue() - APInt(Ty->getBitWidth(), Base);
5635 Case.setValue(
5636 cast<ConstantInt>(ConstantInt::get(Ty, Sub.lshr(ShiftC->getValue()))));
5637 }
5638 return true;
5639}
5640
5641bool SimplifyCFGOpt::SimplifySwitch(SwitchInst *SI, IRBuilder<> &Builder) {
5642 BasicBlock *BB = SI->getParent();
5643
5644 if (isValueEqualityComparison(SI)) {
5645 // If we only have one predecessor, and if it is a branch on this value,
5646 // see if that predecessor totally determines the outcome of this switch.
5647 if (BasicBlock *OnlyPred = BB->getSinglePredecessor())
5648 if (SimplifyEqualityComparisonWithOnlyPredecessor(SI, OnlyPred, Builder))
5649 return requestResimplify();
5650
5651 Value *Cond = SI->getCondition();
5652 if (SelectInst *Select = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(Cond))
5653 if (SimplifySwitchOnSelect(SI, Select))
5654 return requestResimplify();
5655
5656 // If the block only contains the switch, see if we can fold the block
5657 // away into any preds.
5658 if (SI == &*BB->instructionsWithoutDebug().begin())
5659 if (FoldValueComparisonIntoPredecessors(SI, Builder))
5660 return requestResimplify();
5661 }
5662
5663 // Try to transform the switch into an icmp and a branch.
5664 if (TurnSwitchRangeIntoICmp(SI, Builder))
5665 return requestResimplify();
5666
5667 // Remove unreachable cases.
5668 if (eliminateDeadSwitchCases(SI, Options.AC, DL))
5669 return requestResimplify();
5670
5671 if (switchToSelect(SI, Builder, DL, TTI))
5672 return requestResimplify();
5673
5674 if (Options.ForwardSwitchCondToPhi && ForwardSwitchConditionToPHI(SI))
5675 return requestResimplify();
5676
5677 // The conversion from switch to lookup tables results in difficult-to-analyze
5678 // code and makes pruning branches much harder. This is a problem if the
5679 // switch expression itself can still be restricted as a result of inlining or
5680 // CVP. Therefore, only apply this transformation during late stages of the
5681 // optimisation pipeline.
5682 if (Options.ConvertSwitchToLookupTable &&
5683 SwitchToLookupTable(SI, Builder, DL, TTI))
5684 return requestResimplify();
5685
5686 if (ReduceSwitchRange(SI, Builder, DL, TTI))
5687 return requestResimplify();
5688
5689 return false;
5690}
5691
5692bool SimplifyCFGOpt::SimplifyIndirectBr(IndirectBrInst *IBI) {
5693 BasicBlock *BB = IBI->getParent();
5694 bool Changed = false;
5695
5696 // Eliminate redundant destinations.
5697 SmallPtrSet<Value *, 8> Succs;
5698 for (unsigned i = 0, e = IBI->getNumDestinations(); i != e; ++i) {
5699 BasicBlock *Dest = IBI->getDestination(i);
5700 if (!Dest->hasAddressTaken() || !Succs.insert(Dest).second) {
5701 Dest->removePredecessor(BB);
5702 IBI->removeDestination(i);
5703 --i;
5704 --e;
5705 Changed = true;
5706 }
5707 }
5708
5709 if (IBI->getNumDestinations() == 0) {
5710 // If the indirectbr has no successors, change it to unreachable.
5711 new UnreachableInst(IBI->getContext(), IBI);
5712 EraseTerminatorAndDCECond(IBI);
5713 return true;
5714 }
5715
5716 if (IBI->getNumDestinations() == 1) {
5717 // If the indirectbr has one successor, change it to a direct branch.
5718 BranchInst::Create(IBI->getDestination(0), IBI);
5719 EraseTerminatorAndDCECond(IBI);
5720 return true;
5721 }
5722
5723 if (SelectInst *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(IBI->getAddress())) {
5724 if (SimplifyIndirectBrOnSelect(IBI, SI))
5725 return requestResimplify();
5726 }
5727 return Changed;
5728}
5729
5730/// Given an block with only a single landing pad and a unconditional branch
5731/// try to find another basic block which this one can be merged with. This
5732/// handles cases where we have multiple invokes with unique landing pads, but
5733/// a shared handler.
5734///
5735/// We specifically choose to not worry about merging non-empty blocks
5736/// here. That is a PRE/scheduling problem and is best solved elsewhere. In
5737/// practice, the optimizer produces empty landing pad blocks quite frequently
5738/// when dealing with exception dense code. (see: instcombine, gvn, if-else
5739/// sinking in this file)
5740///
5741/// This is primarily a code size optimization. We need to avoid performing
5742/// any transform which might inhibit optimization (such as our ability to
5743/// specialize a particular handler via tail commoning). We do this by not
5744/// merging any blocks which require us to introduce a phi. Since the same
5745/// values are flowing through both blocks, we don't lose any ability to
5746/// specialize. If anything, we make such specialization more likely.
5747///
5748/// TODO - This transformation could remove entries from a phi in the target
5749/// block when the inputs in the phi are the same for the two blocks being
5750/// merged. In some cases, this could result in removal of the PHI entirely.
5751static bool TryToMergeLandingPad(LandingPadInst *LPad, BranchInst *BI,
5752 BasicBlock *BB) {
5753 auto Succ = BB->getUniqueSuccessor();
5754 assert(Succ);
5755 // If there's a phi in the successor block, we'd likely have to introduce
5756 // a phi into the merged landing pad block.
5757 if (isa<PHINode>(*Succ->begin()))
5758 return false;
5759
5760 for (BasicBlock *OtherPred : predecessors(Succ)) {
5761 if (BB == OtherPred)
5762 continue;
5763 BasicBlock::iterator I = OtherPred->begin();
5764 LandingPadInst *LPad2 = dyn_cast<LandingPadInst>(I);
5765 if (!LPad2 || !LPad2->isIdenticalTo(LPad))
5766 continue;
5767 for (++I; isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(I); ++I)
5768 ;
5769 BranchInst *BI2 = dyn_cast<BranchInst>(I);
5770 if (!BI2 || !BI2->isIdenticalTo(BI))
5771 continue;
5772
5773 // We've found an identical block. Update our predecessors to take that
5774 // path instead and make ourselves dead.
5775 SmallPtrSet<BasicBlock *, 16> Preds;
5776 Preds.insert(pred_begin(BB), pred_end(BB));
5777 for (BasicBlock *Pred : Preds) {
5778 InvokeInst *II = cast<InvokeInst>(Pred->getTerminator());
5779 assert(II->getNormalDest() != BB && II->getUnwindDest() == BB &&
5780 "unexpected successor");
5781 II->setUnwindDest(OtherPred);
5782 }
5783
5784 // The debug info in OtherPred doesn't cover the merged control flow that
5785 // used to go through BB. We need to delete it or update it.
5786 for (auto I = OtherPred->begin(), E = OtherPred->end(); I != E;) {
5787 Instruction &Inst = *I;
5788 I++;
5789 if (isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(Inst))
5790 Inst.eraseFromParent();
5791 }
5792
5793 SmallPtrSet<BasicBlock *, 16> Succs;
5794 Succs.insert(succ_begin(BB), succ_end(BB));
5795 for (BasicBlock *Succ : Succs) {
5796 Succ->removePredecessor(BB);
5797 }
5798
5799 IRBuilder<> Builder(BI);
5800 Builder.CreateUnreachable();
5801 BI->eraseFromParent();
5802 return true;
5803 }
5804 return false;
5805}
5806
5807bool SimplifyCFGOpt::SimplifyUncondBranch(BranchInst *BI,
5808 IRBuilder<> &Builder) {
5809 BasicBlock *BB = BI->getParent();
5810 BasicBlock *Succ = BI->getSuccessor(0);
5811
5812 // If the Terminator is the only non-phi instruction, simplify the block.
5813 // If LoopHeader is provided, check if the block or its successor is a loop
5814 // header. (This is for early invocations before loop simplify and
5815 // vectorization to keep canonical loop forms for nested loops. These blocks
5816 // can be eliminated when the pass is invoked later in the back-end.)
5817 // Note that if BB has only one predecessor then we do not introduce new
5818 // backedge, so we can eliminate BB.
5819 bool NeedCanonicalLoop =
5820 Options.NeedCanonicalLoop &&
5821 (LoopHeaders && BB->hasNPredecessorsOrMore(2) &&
5822 (LoopHeaders->count(BB) || LoopHeaders->count(Succ)));
5823 BasicBlock::iterator I = BB->getFirstNonPHIOrDbg()->getIterator();
5824 if (I->isTerminator() && BB != &BB->getParent()->getEntryBlock() &&
5825 !NeedCanonicalLoop && TryToSimplifyUncondBranchFromEmptyBlock(BB))
5826 return true;
5827
5828 // If the only instruction in the block is a seteq/setne comparison against a
5829 // constant, try to simplify the block.
5830 if (ICmpInst *ICI = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(I))
5831 if (ICI->isEquality() && isa<ConstantInt>(ICI->getOperand(1))) {
5832 for (++I; isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(I); ++I)
5833 ;
5834 if (I->isTerminator() &&
5835 tryToSimplifyUncondBranchWithICmpInIt(ICI, Builder))
5836 return true;
5837 }
5838
5839 // See if we can merge an empty landing pad block with another which is
5840 // equivalent.
5841 if (LandingPadInst *LPad = dyn_cast<LandingPadInst>(I)) {
5842 for (++I; isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(I); ++I)
5843 ;
5844 if (I->isTerminator() && TryToMergeLandingPad(LPad, BI, BB))
5845 return true;
5846 }
5847
5848 // If this basic block is ONLY a compare and a branch, and if a predecessor
5849 // branches to us and our successor, fold the comparison into the
5850 // predecessor and use logical operations to update the incoming value
5851 // for PHI nodes in common successor.
5852 if (FoldBranchToCommonDest(BI, nullptr, Options.BonusInstThreshold))
5853 return requestResimplify();
5854 return false;
5855}
5856
5857static BasicBlock *allPredecessorsComeFromSameSource(BasicBlock *BB) {
5858 BasicBlock *PredPred = nullptr;
5859 for (auto *P : predecessors(BB)) {
5860 BasicBlock *PPred = P->getSinglePredecessor();
5861 if (!PPred || (PredPred && PredPred != PPred))
5862 return nullptr;
5863 PredPred = PPred;
5864 }
5865 return PredPred;
5866}
5867
5868bool SimplifyCFGOpt::SimplifyCondBranch(BranchInst *BI, IRBuilder<> &Builder) {
5869 BasicBlock *BB = BI->getParent();
5870 const Function *Fn = BB->getParent();
5871 if (Fn && Fn->hasFnAttribute(Attribute::OptForFuzzing))
5872 return false;
5873
5874 // Conditional branch
5875 if (isValueEqualityComparison(BI)) {
5876 // If we only have one predecessor, and if it is a branch on this value,
5877 // see if that predecessor totally determines the outcome of this
5878 // switch.
5879 if (BasicBlock *OnlyPred = BB->getSinglePredecessor())
5880 if (SimplifyEqualityComparisonWithOnlyPredecessor(BI, OnlyPred, Builder))
5881 return requestResimplify();
5882
5883 // This block must be empty, except for the setcond inst, if it exists.
5884 // Ignore dbg intrinsics.
5885 auto I = BB->instructionsWithoutDebug().begin();
5886 if (&*I == BI) {
5887 if (FoldValueComparisonIntoPredecessors(BI, Builder))
5888 return requestResimplify();
5889 } else if (&*I == cast<Instruction>(BI->getCondition())) {
5890 ++I;
5891 if (&*I == BI && FoldValueComparisonIntoPredecessors(BI, Builder))
5892 return requestResimplify();
5893 }
5894 }
5895
5896 // Try to turn "br (X == 0 | X == 1), T, F" into a switch instruction.
5897 if (SimplifyBranchOnICmpChain(BI, Builder, DL))
5898 return true;
5899
5900 // If this basic block has dominating predecessor blocks and the dominating
5901 // blocks' conditions imply BI's condition, we know the direction of BI.
5902 Optional<bool> Imp = isImpliedByDomCondition(BI->getCondition(), BI, DL);
5903 if (Imp) {
5904 // Turn this into a branch on constant.
5905 auto *OldCond = BI->getCondition();
5906 ConstantInt *TorF = *Imp ? ConstantInt::getTrue(BB->getContext())
5907 : ConstantInt::getFalse(BB->getContext());
5908 BI->setCondition(TorF);
5909 RecursivelyDeleteTriviallyDeadInstructions(OldCond);
5910 return requestResimplify();
5911 }
5912
5913 // If this basic block is ONLY a compare and a branch, and if a predecessor
5914 // branches to us and one of our successors, fold the comparison into the
5915 // predecessor and use logical operations to pick the right destination.
5916 if (FoldBranchToCommonDest(BI, nullptr, Options.BonusInstThreshold))
5917 return requestResimplify();
5918
5919 // We have a conditional branch to two blocks that are only reachable
5920 // from BI. We know that the condbr dominates the two blocks, so see if
5921 // there is any identical code in the "then" and "else" blocks. If so, we
5922 // can hoist it up to the branching block.
5923 if (BI->getSuccessor(0)->getSinglePredecessor()) {
5924 if (BI->getSuccessor(1)->getSinglePredecessor()) {
5925 if (HoistThenElseCodeToIf(BI, TTI))
5926 return requestResimplify();
5927 } else {
5928 // If Successor #1 has multiple preds, we may be able to conditionally
5929 // execute Successor #0 if it branches to Successor #1.
5930 Instruction *Succ0TI = BI->getSuccessor(0)->getTerminator();
5931 if (Succ0TI->getNumSuccessors() == 1 &&
5932 Succ0TI->getSuccessor(0) == BI->getSuccessor(1))
5933 if (SpeculativelyExecuteBB(BI, BI->getSuccessor(0), TTI))
5934 return requestResimplify();
5935 }
5936 } else if (BI->getSuccessor(1)->getSinglePredecessor()) {
5937 // If Successor #0 has multiple preds, we may be able to conditionally
5938 // execute Successor #1 if it branches to Successor #0.
5939 Instruction *Succ1TI = BI->getSuccessor(1)->getTerminator();
5940 if (Succ1TI->getNumSuccessors() == 1 &&
5941 Succ1TI->getSuccessor(0) == BI->getSuccessor(0))
5942 if (SpeculativelyExecuteBB(BI, BI->getSuccessor(1), TTI))
5943 return requestResimplify();
5944 }
5945
5946 // If this is a branch on a phi node in the current block, thread control
5947 // through this block if any PHI node entries are constants.
5948 if (PHINode *PN = dyn_cast<PHINode>(BI->getCondition()))
5949 if (PN->getParent() == BI->getParent())
5950 if (FoldCondBranchOnPHI(BI, DL, Options.AC))
5951 return requestResimplify();
5952
5953 // Scan predecessor blocks for conditional branches.
5954 for (pred_iterator PI = pred_begin(BB), E = pred_end(BB); PI != E; ++PI)
5955 if (BranchInst *PBI = dyn_cast<BranchInst>((*PI)->getTerminator()))
5956 if (PBI != BI && PBI->isConditional())
5957 if (SimplifyCondBranchToCondBranch(PBI, BI, DL))
5958 return requestResimplify();
5959
5960 // Look for diamond patterns.
5961 if (MergeCondStores)
5962 if (BasicBlock *PrevBB = allPredecessorsComeFromSameSource(BB))
5963 if (BranchInst *PBI = dyn_cast<BranchInst>(PrevBB->getTerminator()))
5964 if (PBI != BI && PBI->isConditional())
5965 if (mergeConditionalStores(PBI, BI, DL))
5966 return requestResimplify();
5967
5968 return false;
5969}
5970
5971/// Check if passing a value to an instruction will cause undefined behavior.
5972static bool passingValueIsAlwaysUndefined(Value *V, Instruction *I) {
5973 Constant *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(V);
5974 if (!C)
5975 return false;
5976
5977 if (I->use_empty())
5978 return false;
5979
5980 if (C->isNullValue() || isa<UndefValue>(C)) {
5981 // Only look at the first use, avoid hurting compile time with long uselists
5982 User *Use = *I->user_begin();
5983
5984 // Now make sure that there are no instructions in between that can alter
5985 // control flow (eg. calls)
5986 for (BasicBlock::iterator
5987 i = ++BasicBlock::iterator(I),
5988 UI = BasicBlock::iterator(dyn_cast<Instruction>(Use));
5989 i != UI; ++i)
5990 if (i == I->getParent()->end() || i->mayHaveSideEffects())
5991 return false;
5992
5993 // Look through GEPs. A load from a GEP derived from NULL is still undefined
5994 if (GetElementPtrInst *GEP = dyn_cast<GetElementPtrInst>(Use))
5995 if (GEP->getPointerOperand() == I)
5996 return passingValueIsAlwaysUndefined(V, GEP);
5997
5998 // Look through bitcasts.
5999 if (BitCastInst *BC = dyn_cast<BitCastInst>(Use))
6000 return passingValueIsAlwaysUndefined(V, BC);
6001
6002 // Load from null is undefined.
6003 if (LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(Use))
6004 if (!LI->isVolatile())
6005 return !NullPointerIsDefined(LI->getFunction(),
6006 LI->getPointerAddressSpace());
6007
6008 // Store to null is undefined.
6009 if (StoreInst *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(Use))
6010 if (!SI->isVolatile())
6011 return (!NullPointerIsDefined(SI->getFunction(),
6012 SI->getPointerAddressSpace())) &&
6013 SI->getPointerOperand() == I;
6014
6015 // A call to null is undefined.
6016 if (auto CS = CallSite(Use))
6017 return !NullPointerIsDefined(CS->getFunction()) &&
6018 CS.getCalledValue() == I;
6019 }
6020 return false;
6021}
6022
6023/// If BB has an incoming value that will always trigger undefined behavior
6024/// (eg. null pointer dereference), remove the branch leading here.
6025static bool removeUndefIntroducingPredecessor(BasicBlock *BB) {
6026 for (PHINode &PHI : BB->phis())
6027 for (unsigned i = 0, e = PHI.getNumIncomingValues(); i != e; ++i)
6028 if (passingValueIsAlwaysUndefined(PHI.getIncomingValue(i), &PHI)) {
6029 Instruction *T = PHI.getIncomingBlock(i)->getTerminator();
6030 IRBuilder<> Builder(T);
6031 if (BranchInst *BI = dyn_cast<BranchInst>(T)) {
6032 BB->removePredecessor(PHI.getIncomingBlock(i));
6033 // Turn uncoditional branches into unreachables and remove the dead
6034 // destination from conditional branches.
6035 if (BI->isUnconditional())
6036 Builder.CreateUnreachable();
6037 else
6038 Builder.CreateBr(BI->getSuccessor(0) == BB ? BI->getSuccessor(1)
6039 : BI->getSuccessor(0));
6040 BI->eraseFromParent();
6041 return true;
6042 }
6043 // TODO: SwitchInst.
6044 }
6045
6046 return false;
6047}
6048
6049bool SimplifyCFGOpt::simplifyOnce(BasicBlock *BB) {
6050 bool Changed = false;
6051
6052 assert(BB && BB->getParent() && "Block not embedded in function!");
6053 assert(BB->getTerminator() && "Degenerate basic block encountered!");
6054
6055 // Remove basic blocks that have no predecessors (except the entry block)...
6056 // or that just have themself as a predecessor. These are unreachable.
6057 if ((pred_empty(BB) && BB != &BB->getParent()->getEntryBlock()) ||
6058 BB->getSinglePredecessor() == BB) {
6059 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Removing BB: \n" << *BB);
6060 DeleteDeadBlock(BB);
6061 return true;
6062 }
6063
6064 // Check to see if we can constant propagate this terminator instruction
6065 // away...
6066 Changed |= ConstantFoldTerminator(BB, true);
6067
6068 // Check for and eliminate duplicate PHI nodes in this block.
6069 Changed |= EliminateDuplicatePHINodes(BB);
6070
6071 // Check for and remove branches that will always cause undefined behavior.
6072 Changed |= removeUndefIntroducingPredecessor(BB);
6073
6074 // Merge basic blocks into their predecessor if there is only one distinct
6075 // pred, and if there is only one distinct successor of the predecessor, and
6076 // if there are no PHI nodes.
6077 if (MergeBlockIntoPredecessor(BB))
6078 return true;
6079
6080 if (SinkCommon && Options.SinkCommonInsts)
6081 Changed |= SinkCommonCodeFromPredecessors(BB);
6082
6083 IRBuilder<> Builder(BB);
6084
6085 // If there is a trivial two-entry PHI node in this basic block, and we can
6086 // eliminate it, do so now.
6087 if (auto *PN = dyn_cast<PHINode>(BB->begin()))
6088 if (PN->getNumIncomingValues() == 2)
6089 Changed |= FoldTwoEntryPHINode(PN, TTI, DL);
6090
6091 Builder.SetInsertPoint(BB->getTerminator());
6092 if (auto *BI = dyn_cast<BranchInst>(BB->getTerminator())) {
6093 if (BI->isUnconditional()) {
6094 if (SimplifyUncondBranch(BI, Builder))
6095 return true;
6096 } else {
6097 if (SimplifyCondBranch(BI, Builder))
6098 return true;
6099 }
6100 } else if (auto *RI = dyn_cast<ReturnInst>(BB->getTerminator())) {
6101 if (SimplifyReturn(RI, Builder))
6102 return true;
6103 } else if (auto *RI = dyn_cast<ResumeInst>(BB->getTerminator())) {
6104 if (SimplifyResume(RI, Builder))
6105 return true;
6106 } else if (auto *RI = dyn_cast<CleanupReturnInst>(BB->getTerminator())) {
6107 if (SimplifyCleanupReturn(RI))
6108 return true;
6109 } else if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<SwitchInst>(BB->getTerminator())) {
6110 if (SimplifySwitch(SI, Builder))
6111 return true;
6112 } else if (auto *UI = dyn_cast<UnreachableInst>(BB->getTerminator())) {
6113 if (SimplifyUnreachable(UI))
6114 return true;
6115 } else if (auto *IBI = dyn_cast<IndirectBrInst>(BB->getTerminator())) {
6116 if (SimplifyIndirectBr(IBI))
6117 return true;
6118 }
6119
6120 return Changed;
6121}
6122
6123bool SimplifyCFGOpt::run(BasicBlock *BB) {
6124 bool Changed = false;
6125
6126 // Repeated simplify BB as long as resimplification is requested.
6127 do {
6128 Resimplify = false;
6129
6130 // Perform one round of simplifcation. Resimplify flag will be set if
6131 // another iteration is requested.
6132 Changed |= simplifyOnce(BB);
6133 } while (Resimplify);
6134
6135 return Changed;
6136}
6137
6138bool llvm::simplifyCFG(BasicBlock *BB, const TargetTransformInfo &TTI,
6139 const SimplifyCFGOptions &Options,
6140 SmallPtrSetImpl<BasicBlock *> *LoopHeaders) {
6141 return SimplifyCFGOpt(TTI, BB->getModule()->getDataLayout(), LoopHeaders,
6142 Options)
6143 .run(BB);
6144}
